.com/p/BCGM29Ul6q4/|title=Daddy Yankee and Chris Jeday working on ''King Daddy II'' at Master House Studios|publisher=instagram.com|date=February 22, 2016|accessdate=October 20, 2016}}</ref> <br />{{small|([[Doral, Florida]], United States)}}}}}}\n| genre      = [[Reggaeton]]\n| length     =\n| label      = [[El Cartel Records|El Cartel]]\n| producer   = {{hlist|Chris Jeday|Gaby Music|Jumbo|Los Evo Jedis}}\n| prev_title = [[El Imperio Nazza#El Imperio Nazza King Daddy Edition (2013)|King Daddy]]\n| prev_year  = 2013\n| year       = TBA\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = El Disco Duro\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[S\u00edgueme y Te Sigo]]\n | single1date = March 12, 2015\n | single2     = Vaiv\u00e9n\n | single2date = September 17, 2015\n | single3     = [[Shaky Shaky]]\n | single3date = April 8, 2016\n | single4     = [[Otra Cosa (Daddy Yankee song)|Otra Cosa]]\n | single4date = December 9, 2016\n | single5     = [[La Rompe Corazones]]\n | single5date = January 6, 2017\n | single6     = [[Vuelve (Daddy Yankee song)|Vuelve]]\n | single6date = September 29, 2017\n | single7     = [[Dura (song)|Dura]]\n | single7date = January 18, 2018\n | single8     = [[Hielo (song)|Hielo]]\n | single8date = May 18, 2018\n | single9     = Zum Zum\n | single9date = June 15, 2018\n | single10     = [[Adictiva]]\n | single10date = November 8, 2018\n | single11     = [[Con Calma]]\n | single11date = January 24, 2019\n | single12     = [[Si Supieras]]\n | single12date = June 28, 2019\n | single13     = [[Que Tire Pa Lante]]\n | single13date = October 18, 2019\n | single14     = Definitivamente\n | single14date = January 31, 2020\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''El Disco Duro''''' is the upcoming seventh studio album (fourteenth overall) by Puerto Rican rapper [[Daddy Yankee]], originally scheduled to be released during early 2017. Its original title was ''King Daddy II: Elemento DY'', a [[sequel]] to his previous album ''[[El Imperio Nazza#King Daddy Edition|King Daddy]]'', produced by Los De La Nazza, a production duo that worked with Daddy Yankee from 2007 to 2014. The album will include \"[[S\u00edgueme y Te Sigo]]\", \"Vaiv\u00e9n\" and \"[[Shaky Shaky]]\" as its singles, which were released between March 2015 and April 2016. Its release date is yet to be announced.\n\n==Background==\n[[File:DaddyYankee.jpg|thumb|left|Daddy Yankee in 2006.|150px]]\n''El Disco Duro'' (originally titled ''King Daddy II: Elemento DY'')<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.univision.com/puerto-rico/wkaq/daddy-yankee-se-encuentra-en-el-estudio-finalizando-su-proximo-album|title=Daddy Yankee se encuentra en el estudio finalizando su pr\u00f3ximo \u00e1lbum|trans-title=Daddy Yankee is in the studio finalizing his upcoming album|publisher=Univisi\u00f3n|language=Spanish|date=January 13, 2016|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.elnuevoherald.com/entretenimiento/musica/article47728830.html|title=Daddy Yankee y Don Omar se van al duelo para disputarse corona del reguet\u00f3n|work=[[El Nuevo Herald]]|language=Spanish|date=December 3, 2015|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> was going to be the sequel of his previous mixtape ''[[El Imperio Nazza#King Daddy Edition|King Daddy]]'', released in October 2013, which became the first digital-only Latin album that managed to rank within the top 10 on the US [[Top Latin Albums]] chart.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin-notas/5785843/inside-daddy-yankees-digital-only-king-album|title=Inside Daddy Yankee's Digital-Only 'King' Album|work=Billboard|date=November 11, 2013|last=Cobo|first=Leila|accessdate=August 20, 2016}}</ref> Two months after the release of ''King Daddy'', Daddy Yankee announced that there was going to be a physical version of the album, with exclusive bonus tracks, planned to be released during 2014, but it was not published after all.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.informador.com.mx/entretenimiento/2014/506146/6/daddy-yankee-lanzara-en-formato-fisico-el-album-king-daddy.htm|title=Daddy Yankee lanzar\u00e1 en formato f\u00edsico el \u00e1lbum 'King Daddy'|publisher=informador.com.mx|language=spanish|date=January 6, 2014|accessdate=October 28, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.elheraldo.hn/vida/600816-220/daddy-yankee-lanza-nuevo-disco-y-va-por-masm|title=Daddy Yankee lanza nuevo disco y va por m\u00e1s|work=El Heraldo|language=Spanish|date=April 7, 2014|accessdate=August 18, 2017|location=Honduras}}{{Dead link|date=December 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nThe Puerto Rican production duo [[Los de la Nazza]], which had been working with Daddy Yankee since 2007, left [[El Cartel Records]] and stopped being his main producers in order to focus on their careers. Chris Jeday and Gaby Music were hired as the album's main producers during late 2014. ''El Disco Duro'' was officially announced during mid-2014 as ''King Daddy II'' with the promotion of the single \"S\u00e1bado Rebelde\" featuring Puerto Rican duo [[Plan B (duo)|Plan B]], released on October 31.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.elnuevoherald.com/entretenimiento/musica/article16902242.html|title=Daddy Yankee sigue siendo el Rey|trans-title=Daddy Yankee is still the king|work=[[El Nuevo Herald]]|last=Vargas|first=Doraluz|language=Spanish|date=March 30, 2015|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn September 10, he was urgently moved to a nearby hospital in [[Cali]], [[Colombia]], where he was set to perform later that night. Daddy Yankee suffered a rise in blood pressure, [[hypoglycemia]] and dehydration, which almost caused him to suffer a heart attack before being treated by doctors. His condition improved and he was sent to rest in his native Puerto Rico, but had to cancel other concerts in Colombia.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.peopleenespanol.com/article/daddy-yankee-estuvo-al-borde-del-ataque-cardiaco|title=Daddy Yankee: los problemas de salud que le llevaron al hospital|publisher=peopleenespanol.com|last=Mabry Para\u00edso|first=Alexander|language=spanish|date=September 13, 2016|accessdate=October 17, 2016}}</ref> On October 19, he confirmed that his hypoglycemia worsened and turned into a [[prediabetes]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.elheraldo.hn/entretenimiento/1009872-466/reguetonero-daddy-yankee-confirma-grave-enfermedad|title=Reguetonero Daddy Yankee confirma grave enfermedad|publisher=eheraldo.hn|language=spanish|date=October 19, 2016|accessdate=October 20, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1953723-daddy-yankee-rompio-el-silencio-sobre-la-enfermedad-que-padecen-el-y-una-de-sus-hijas|title=Daddy Yankee rompi\u00f3 el silencio sobre la enfermedad que padecen \u00e9l y una de sus hijas|publisher=lanacion.com.ar|language=spanish|date=November 5, 2016|accessdate=November 6, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2017, he was featured on the reggaeton-pop single \"[[Despacito]]\" by Puerto Rican singer [[Luis Fonsi]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7669777/luis-fonsi-highest-debut-hot-latin-songs-chart|title=Luis Fonsi Earns His Highest Debut Ever on Hot Latin Songs Chart|work=Billboard|last=Mendizabal|first=Amaya|date=January 26, 2017|accessdate=February 26, 2017}}</ref> The song was a worldwide success, topping the charts of 45 countries, including a number 1 spot on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], the first for a primarily Spanish-language song since \"[[Macarena (song)|Macarena]]\" by [[Los del R\u00edo]] in 1996.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7793159/luis-fonsi-daddy-yankee-despacito-justin-bieber-number-one|title=Luis Fonsi & Daddy Yankee's 'Despacito' With Justin Bieber: No. 1 on the Billboard Hot 100 This Week|work=Billboard|first=Gary|last=Trust|date=May 15, 2017|accessdate=May 16, 2017}}</ref> The success of the song led Daddy Yankee to become the most listened artist worldwide on the streaming service [[Spotify]] on July 9, 2017, being the first Latin artist to do so.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/daddy-yankee-is-1-on-spotify-1st-latin-artist-to-do-so/2017/07/09/42a78bb2-64da-11e7-94ab-5b1f0ff459df_story.html|title=Daddy Yankee is #1 on Spotify; 1st Latin artist to do so|publisher=[[Washington Post]]|last=Ratner-Arias|first=Sigal|date=July 9, 2017|accessdate=July 9, 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170709221642/https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/daddy-yankee-is-1-on-spotify-1st-latin-artist-to-do-so/2017/07/09/42a78bb2-64da-11e7-94ab-5b1f0ff459df_story.html|archivedate=July 9, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.vibe.com/2017/07/daddy-yankee-number-1-spotify/|title=Daddy Yankee Breaks Barriers Becoming Top Streamed Artist On Spotify|publisher=[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]]|last=Pickens|first=Ashley|date=July 10, 2017|accessdate=July 10, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2017, Daddy Yankee announced a global partnership with [[Zumba|Zumba Fitness]], in which he would record exclusive tracks for the Zumba Instructor Network.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.vibe.com/2017/03/daddy-yankee-zumba-fitness-hula-hoop-dance/|title=Daddy Yankee Teams Up With Zumba For \"Hula Hoop\" Workout|publisher=[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]]|last=Imarenezor|first=Christine|date=March 8, 2017|accessdate=August 19, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://zlife.zumba.com/daddy-yankee-zumba-announce-global-partnership-support-artists-new-single-hula-hoop/|title=Daddy Yankee and Zumba Announce Global Partnership in Support of Artist\u2019s New Single \"Hula Hoop\"|publisher=zlife.zumba.com|date=March 3, 2017|accessdate=August 19, 2017}}</ref> On March 15, 2017, Daddy Yankee was recognized as Artist/Songwriter of the Year by the [[American Society of Composers, Authors and Publishers]] during the 25th Annual ASCAP Latin Music Awards.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7727807/daddy-yankee-joss-favela-ascap-latin-awards-winners|title=Daddy Yankee, Joss Favela Win Top Honors at ASCAP Latin Awards|work=Billboard|last=Cobo|first=Leila|date=March 15, 2017|accessdate=March 16, 2017}}</ref> A day later, he received a Puerto Rican Walk of Fame Star in San Juan, becoming the first urban act to do so.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.meridiano90.com/1829_eeuu/4402017_paseo-fama-de-puerto-rico-ya-cuenta-con-estrellas-a-reguetonero-y-deportistas.html|title=Paseo Fama de Puerto Rico ya cuenta con estrellas a reggaetonero y deportistas|publisher=meridiano90.com|language=Spanish|date=March 16, 2017|accessdate=March 16, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170317234007/http://www.meridiano90.com/1829_eeuu/4402017_paseo-fama-de-puerto-rico-ya-cuenta-con-estrellas-a-reguetonero-y-deportistas.html|archive-date=March 17, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7728541/daddy-yankee-ednita-nazario-honored-puerto-rico|title=Daddy Yankee & Ednita Nazario Honored by the Puerto Rico Hall of Fame|work=Billboard|last=Fernandez|first=Suzette|date=March 17, 2017|accessdate=March 19, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\n\"[[S\u00edgueme y Te Sigo]]\" is a dance love song written by Daddy Yankee, Chris Jeday and Luis \"Wichi\" Ort\u00edz Rivera, inspired by [[social networks]] but not centred on them, and mixes reggaeton with Latin pop, including an electric guitar riff.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vivelohoy.com/entretenimiento/8446109/video-sigueme-y-te-sigo-de-daddy-yankee|title=S\u00edgueme Y Te Sigo, de Daddy Yankee|publisher=vivelohoy.com|language=spanish|date=May 11, 2015|accessdate=August 19, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160827152720/http://www.vivelohoy.com/entretenimiento/8446109/video-sigueme-y-te-sigo-de-daddy-yankee|archive-date=August 27, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n\"Vaiv\u00e9n\" is a [[moombahton]] song written by Daddy Yankee, Luis \"Wichi\" Ort\u00edz Rivera and the producer Chris Jeday.\n\n\"[[Shaky Shaky]]\" is a reggaeton song born as a [[Freestyle rap|freestyle]] during early December 2015, and was later recorded by the production duo Los Evo Jedis.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.primerahora.com/entretenimiento/farandula/nota/daddyyankeecompartesushakyshaky-1147337/|title=Daddy Yankee comparte su \"Shaky Shaky\"|publisher=primerahora.com|language=Spanish|date=April 11, 2016|accessdate=August 20, 2016}}</ref> According to Daddy Yankee, the main vocals were recorded in one take and the song musically mixes sounds from old and new school reggaeton.<ref name=\"shaky\">{{cite web |url= http://www.latintimes.com/daddy-yankee-shaky-shaky-premiere-5-reasons-why-you-have-watch-el-cangri-music-video-392998|title=Daddy Yankee 'Shaky Shaky' Premiere: 5 Reasons Why You Have To Watch 'El Cangri' Music Video|publisher=Latin Times|last=Valdez|first=Maria|date=July 15, 2016|accessdate=August 22, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"shaky new old\">{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7556771/daddy-yankee-shaky-shaky-number-1-hot-latin-songs-chart|title=Daddy Yankee Celebrates 'Shaky Shaky' Hitting No. 1 on Hot Latin Songs Chart|last=Mendizabal|first=Amaya|work=Billboard|date=October 25, 2016|accessdate=October 25, 2016}}</ref> The [[keyboard bass]] line was based on the one from the single \"Murder She Wrote\" by [[Chaka Demus & Pliers]], released in 1992.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.nytimes.com/2016/09/03/arts/music/playlist-young-thug-cherry-glazerr-sylvan-esso.html|title=The Playlist: Young Thug Turns the Summer's Big Meme Into a Standout Track|publisher=nytimes.com|last1=Pareles|first1=Jon|last2=Caramanica|first2=Jon|last3=Chinen|first3=Nate|date=September 2, 2016|accessdate=September 14, 2016}}</ref> It also includes a repeating sample of a horse's neigh from [[Mel and Tim]]'s \"Good Guys Only Win in the Movies\" (1970), which became popular after [[Cypress Hill]]'s \"[[Insane in the Brain]]\" (1993).<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.whosampled.com/sample/854/Cypress-Hill-Insane-in-the-Brain-Mel-%26-Tim-Good-Guys-Only-Win-in-the-Movies/|title=Cypress Hill's 'Insane in the Brain' sample of Mel & Tim's 'Good Guys Only Win in the Movies'|publisher=whosampled.com|accessdate=October 25, 2016}}</ref>\n\n\"Otra Cosa\" features Dominican singer [[Natti Natasha]] and is a fusion between reggaeton, dancehall and moombahton music written by Daddy Yankee, Natti Natasha and Puerto Rican producer Haze.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.univision.com/noticias/edicion-digital/daddy-yankee-y-natti-natasha-estrenan-otra-cosa-su-cancion-para-ponerle-ritmo-al-fin-de-ano-video|title=Daddy Yankee y Natti Natasha estrenan \u2018Otra cosa\u2019, su canci\u00f3n para ponerle ritmo al fin de a\u00f1o|publisher=Univisi\u00f3n|language=Spanish|date=December 8, 2016|accessdate=August 17, 2017}} 1:20\u20131:40</ref><ref name=\"otra cosa int\">{{cite web |url= https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Aaibwc0jF6w|title=Entrevista a Daddy Yankee y Dominicana Natti Natasha|type=Video|publisher=YouTube|language=Spanish|date=January 26, 2017|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> The lyrics are about [[lovesickness]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.diariolasamericas.com/cultura/daddy-yankee-y-natti-natasha-estrenan-videoclip-otra-cosa-n4113444|title=Daddy Yankee y Natti Natasha estrenan videoclip de \"Otra cosa\"|trans-title=Daddy Yankee and Natti Natasha premiere \"Otra Cosa\" video clip|work=[[Diario Las Am\u00e9ricas]]|language=Spanish|date=January 27, 2017|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> The concept of the song was brought to Daddy Yankee by Haze and Natti Natasha in order to be included on the track listing of ''La Super F\u00f3rmula'', a [[Pina Records]] studio album by various artists.<ref name=\"otra cosa int\"/><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.metro.pr/pr/entretener/2016/12/09/daddy-yankee-natti-natasha-lanzan-otra-cosa.html|title=Daddy Yankee y Natti Natasha lanzan \"Otra cosa\"|publisher=metro.pr|language=Spanish|date=December 9, 2016|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\n\"La Rompe Corazones\" features Puerto Rican singer Ozuna and was written by Daddy Yankee, Ozuna, Chris Jeday and Puerto Rican songwriter Jes\u00fas \"Benny Benni\" Benitez Hiraldo.<ref name=\"Billboard\">{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f[0]=ss_chart_search_title%3A%22La%20Rompe%20Corazones%22&f[1]=itm_field_chart_id%3A363&refine=1|title=''Billboard'' Chart Search \u2013 La Rompe Corazones \u2013 Daddy Yankee X Ozuna \u2013 Hot Latin Songs|work=Billboard|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> The song tells the story of a lovesick woman who no longer trusts her relationships, taking revenge on other men through her frustration.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.daddyyankee.com/master-76|title=Daddy Yankee habla qu\u00e9 lo inspir\u00f3 en La Rompe Corazones|publisher=daddyyankee.com|date=January 11, 2017|accessdate=January 13, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\n[[File:North Miami FL Criteria Studios01.jpg|thumb|right|[[Criteria Studios]] was one of various studios the album was recorded at.|220px]]\nThe first known recording session for ''El Disco Duro'' with producers Chris Jeday and Gaby Music was held in December 2014.<ref name=\"Instagram\">{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/wL6WlQF6ux/|title=GRINDIN KING DADDY 2 ... 24 horas en el estudio y seguimos|publisher=Instagram|author1=Chris Jeday|author2=Daddy Yankee|type=Post|language=spanish|date=December 4, 2014|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref> The last known session was carried out in May 2017 with the recording of the track \"Percocet\".<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/BE2YRkArK0V/|title=El tema controversial del album: \"PERCOCET\"|publisher=Instagram|author=Daddy Yankee|type=Post|language=Spanish|date=May 1, 2016|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/BE3EdLBl6s4/|title=Dandole \ud83d\udc8a\ud83d\udc8a PERCOCET \ud83d\udc8a\ud83d\udc8a\ud83c\udfbc\ud83c\udfbc @daddyyankee @gabymusic la musa a 100|publisher=Instagram|author=Chris Jeday|type=Post|language=Spanish|date=May 1, 2016|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> The recording was resumed during mid-October 2016 with Daddy Yankee and Dominican singer [[Natti Natasha]] recording the single \"Otra Cosa\" for [[Pina Records]]' upcoming studio album ''La Super F\u00f3rmula''.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/BLe-HAwhh2n/|title=Trabajando con la baby @nattinatasha \ud83d\ude18\ud83c\udf39\ud83c\udf39@pinarecords1|publisher=Instagram|author=Daddy Yankee|type=Post|language=spanish|date=October 12, 2016|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> However, Daddy Yankee managed to include the track on ''El Disco Duro'' during December 2016.<ref name=\"Vernon\">{{cite web |url= http://www.univision.com/musica/reggaeton/exclusiva-todo-sobre-otra-cosa-la-nueva-cancion-de-daddy-yankee-y-natti-natasha|title=Exclusiva: Todo sobre 'Otra cosa', la nueva canci\u00f3n de Daddy Yankee y Natti Natasha|language=Spanish|publisher=Univisi\u00f3n|last=Vernon|first=Beatriz|date=December 7, 2016|accessdate=December 14, 2016}}</ref> On February 21, 2017, Daddy Yankee uploaded an image on his official [[Instagram]] account listening to the album.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/BQy4NEwgLLx/|title=Studio \ud83c\udfa7.. Escuchando\ud83d\udc42\ud83c\udffc EL DISCO DURO \ud83d\udcc0\ud83d\udcbf\ud83d\udcc0\ud83d\udcbf\ud83d\udcc0|publisher=Instagram|author=Daddy Yankee|type=Post|language=spanish|date=February 21, 2017|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\nStudios where the album was recorded includes Daddy Yankee's El Cartel Studios in [[Santurce, San Juan, Puerto Rico]], Chris Jeday's Music Capos Studios in Puerto Rico, [[Criteria Studios]] in [[Miami, Florida, USA]], and Master House Studios in [[Doral, Florida|Doral, Florida, USA]].<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/BEvvYdWmXQX/|title=There's fire in Studio D ~courtesy of Daddy Yankee. \u2668\ufe0f Some artists like to record vocals in the control room DY is one of them!|publisher=Instagram|author=Criteria Recording Studios|type=Post|date=April 28, 2016|accessdate=October 6, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/BCGM29Ul6q4/|title=Kd2 @daddyyankee|publisher=Instagram|author=Chris Jeday|type=Post|date=February 22, 2016|accessdate=October 20, 2016}}</ref>\n\n\"S\u00edgueme y Te Sigo\" was mixed at El Cartel Studios in February 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/zPycZPF6m3/|title=MUSIC CAPOS $$$ MIXING SECTION WITH @earcandypro @daddyyankee SIGUEME Y TE SIGO|publisher=Instagram|author=Chris Jeday|type=Post|language=spanish|date=February 18, 2015|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/zMvKxmF6pR/|title=Laborando con @daddyyankee @gabymusic y @earcandypro -TEMA SIGUEME Y TE SIGO|publisher=Instagram|author=Chris Jeday|type=Post|language=spanish|date=February 17, 2015|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/ykkh-WF6in/|title=Tema: \"SIGUEME Y TE SIGO\" #KD \u264a\ufe0f. Bastagazo!! HIT!. Que pensaban que na' m\u00e1s estaba puesto pa' la calle? No confundan mi hobby con mi NEGOCIO. Atte. EL QUE SIEMPRE LES CAMBIA EL JUEGO! @daddyyankee @chrisjeday @gabymusic|publisher=Instagram|author=Daddy Yankee|type=Post|language=spanish|date=February 1, 2015|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> Sound test for \"Vaiv\u00e9n\" was held by Chris Jeday at Music Capos Studios during early August 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/6bF5xxwSkG/|title=VAIVEN PRUEBA DE SONIDO DONDE TODO COMIENZA \ud83c\udfb9\ud83c\udfb9\ud83c\udfbc\ud83c\udfbc CREANDO MUSIC CAPOS @daddyyankee @gabymusic WORLDWIDE SOUND|publisher=Instagram|author=Chris Jeday|type=Post|language=spanish|date=August 15, 2015|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> The song was later mixed at Criteria Studios and at El Cartel Studios the same month.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/63c1hrl6qX/|title=SIEMPRE BUSCANDO LA PERFECCION MIXING SESSION #ELVAIVEN DY @daddyyankee EN LOS CONTROLES LOS DUROS @earcandypro @gabymusic MUSIC CAPOS #ELVAIVEN WORLDWIDE SOUND|publisher=Instagram|author=Chris Jeday|type=Post|language=spanish|date=August 26, 2015|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/61U8fWF6qJ/|title=MIXING #ELVAIVEN CON @daddyyankee y @gabymusic CARTEL|publisher=Instagram|author=Chris Jeday|type=Post|language=spanish|date=August 26, 2015|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\nDaddy Yankee confirmed on October 26, 2016 during a meeting with Zumba fitness creator [[Beto Perez]] at [[Pina Records]] that ''El Disco Duro'' will be released during early 2017, most likely during January or February.<ref name=\"releasedate\">{{cite web |url= http://www.univision.com/musica/reggaeton/daddy-yankee-dio-un-adelanto-de-su-nuevo-disco-al-fundador-de-zumba|title=Daddy Yankee dio un adelanto de su nuevo disco al fundador de Zumba|publisher=Univisi\u00f3n|language=spanish|last=Miserachi|first=Raquel|date=October 26, 2016|accessdate=October 27, 2016}}</ref> On June 21, 2017, Daddy Yankee stated that he postponed the album's release due to finding more successful the release of singles instead of an entire record.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FU-_cDQMvL8|title=Daddy Yankee en directo en \"Anda Ya!\", 21 de Junio|quote=I was going to release the album but for some reason single after single is working better.|publisher=YouTube|language=Spanish|date=June 21, 2017|accessdate=August 19, 2017}} 17:33\u201318:06</ref> In December 2014, ''Billboard'' magazine added digital and streaming information to count sales: 1,000 digital songs sales and 1,500 song streams separately equal one album sale, which may affect the chart placement of the album. Considered on-demand audio services includes [[Spotify]], [[Google Play]], [[Beats Music]] and [[Xbox Music]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6320099/billboard-200-makeover-streams-digital-tracks|title=Billboard 200 Makeover: Album Chart to Incorporate Streams & Track Sales|work=Billboard|date=November 19, 2014|accessdate=November 3, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Singles===\n{{Listen\n|filename=Daddy Yankee - Shaky Shaky.ogg\n|title=\"Shaky Shaky\"\n|description=A 29-second sample of \"[[Shaky Shaky]]\". The song blends sounds from old and new school reggaeton. It became a number-one hit single on the US Latin and Tropical Songs charts.\n|format=[[Ogg]]}}\n\n\"[[S\u00edgueme y Te Sigo]]\" was released as the first single on March 12, 2015. It peaked at number 6 on the US [[Hot Latin Songs]] chart on June 13, 2015 and at number 5 on [[Tropical Songs]] on April 18, 2015.<ref name=\"hotlatin 2\">{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/300083/daddy-yankee/chart?page=1&f=363|title=Daddy Yankee \u2013 Chart history \u2013 Hot Latin Songs|work=Billboard|page=2|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"tropical 1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/300083/daddy-yankee/chart?f=340|title=Daddy Yankee \u2013 Chart history \u2013 Tropical Songs|work=Billboard|page=1|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> Internationally, the song peaked at number 12 in Spain, at number 32 in Venezuela, and at number 198 in France.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.promusicae.es/listas/semana/2923-canciones-semana-28-2015.pdf |title=Top 100 Canciones \u2013 SEMANA 28: del 06.07.2015 al 09.07.2015  |publisher=promusicae.es|language=spanish|accessdate=August 26, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"siguemevaiven\">{{cite web|url=http://national-report.com.ve/wp-content/uploads/TOP-100-DETECCIONES-SEMANAL-31.pdf|title=Top 100 Detecciones Semanal Semana 31 del 2016|publisher=national-report.com.ve|language=spanish|date=September 1, 2016|accessdate=October 21, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161101104544/http://national-report.com.ve/wp-content/uploads/TOP-100-DETECCIONES-SEMANAL-31.pdf|archive-date=November 1, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.snepmusique.com/tops-semaine/top-singles-telecharges/?ye=2015&we=28 |title=Le Top de la semaine : Top Singles T\u00e9l\u00e9charg\u00e9s \u2013 Semaine du Aout 14, 2015 |publisher=snepmusique.com|language=french|date=August 14, 2015|accessdate=August 26, 2016}}</ref> It was certified 2\u00d7 platinum by the [[PROMUSICAE]], platinum by the IFPI Chile, and gold by the [[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana|FIMI]].<ref name=\"siguemepromusicae\">{{cite web |url= http://www.elportaldemusica.es/cancion-10039-18054-daddy-yankee-sigueme-y-te-sigo|title=Daddy Yankee \u2013 S\u00edgueme y Te Sigo|publisher=elportaldemusica.es|accessdate=August 19, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"ifpichile\">{{cite web|url=http://www.daddyyankee.com/master-71|title=Chile Recibe al Rey del Reggaeton con Triple Disco de Platino por sus sencillos ''Shaky Shaky'', ''S\u00edgueme y Te Sigo'' y ''Vaiv\u00e9n''|publisher=daddyyankee.com|language=spanish|date=November 29, 2016|accessdate=November 29, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161220073558/http://www.daddyyankee.com/master-71|archive-date=December 20, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"shakyfimi\">{{cite web |url= http://www.fimi.it/certificazioni#/category:tutte/year:2016/page:0/term:Daddy|title=Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana \u2013 Certificazioni \u2013 Daddy Yankee  2016|publisher=fimi.it|language=italian|accessdate=January 23, 2017}}</ref>\n\n\"Vaiv\u00e9n\" was released as the second single on September 17, 2015. Although the song does not have an official music video, it managed to peak at number 7 on the US Hot Latin Songs chart and at number 3 on Tropical Songs, both on January 23, 2016.<ref name=\"hotlatin 2\"/><ref name=\"tropical 1\"/> Internationally, the single reached number 19 in Spain and number 34 in Venezuela.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.promusicae.es/listas/semana/3003-canciones-semana-43-2015.pdf|title=Top 100 Canciones \u2013 SEMANA 43: del 16.10.2015 al 22.10.2015  |publisher=promusicae.es|language=spanish|accessdate=August 26, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"siguemevaiven\"/> It received a platinum certification by the PROMUSICAE and the IFPI Chile.<ref name=\"vaivenpromusicae\">{{cite web |url= http://www.elportaldemusica.es/cancion-11030-19571-daddy-yankee-vaiven|title=Daddy Yankee \u2013 Vaiv\u00e9n|publisher=elportaldemusica.es|accessdate=August 19, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"ifpichile\"/>\n\n\"[[Shaky Shaky]]\" was released as the third single on April 8, 2016, although it was originally planned as a gift from Yankee to his fans for 2015 Christmas. The song reached the number 1 spot on the US Hot Latin Songs and [[Tropical Songs]] charts on November 5 and August 20, 2016, respectively.<ref name=\"hotlatin 1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/300083/daddy-yankee/chart?f=363|title=Daddy Yankee \u2013 Chart history \u2013 Hot Latin Songs|work=Billboard|page=1|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"tropical 1\"/> It became his fourth No. 1 song on the Hot Latin Songs chart and his first one since February 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7556711/daddy-yankee-hot-latin-songs-shaky-shaky|title=Hitting No. 1, Daddy Yankee Style: Listen to His 4 Biggest Chart Hits|work=Billboard|last=Fernandez|first=Suzette|date=October 25, 2016|accessdate=October 25, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"hotlatin 1\"/> It also peaked at number 88 in the [[Billboard Hot 100|United States]], becoming Daddy Yankee's first entry on the Hot 100 since the debut of \"[[Impacto]]\" on May 26, 2007.<ref name=\"hot100\">{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/300083/daddy-yankee/chart?f=379|title=Daddy Yankee \u2013 Chart history \u2013 The Hot 100|work=Billboard|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100/2007-05-26|title=The Hot 100 \u2013 Week of May 26, 2007|work=Billboard|date=May 26, 2007|accessdate=January 15, 2017}}</ref> Internationally, the song peaked at number 1 in Mexico and the Dominican Republic, at number 4 in Colombia, at number 11 in Guatemala, at number 14 in Uruguay, at number 25 in Spain, and at number 42 in Venezuela.<ref>International peaks for \"Shaky Shaky\":\n*M\u00e9xico: {{cite web|url=http://monitorlatino.com/shaky-shaky-sobre-mi-como-no-queriendo-y-let-me-love-you-las-canciones-con-mas-audiencia-en-mexico/|title=\"Shaky, shaky\", \"Sobre m\u00ed\", \"Como no queriendo\" y \"Let me love you\" las canciones con m\u00e1s audiencia en M\u00e9xico|last=Rivera|first=Nayeli|publisher=Monitor Latino|language=spanish|date=October 3, 2016|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}\n*Dominican Republic: {{cite web|url=http://monitorlatino.com/daddy-yankee-anthony-santos-jose-montoro-los-mas-sonados-de-republica-dominicana/|title=Daddy Yankee, Anthony Santos, Jos\u00e9 Montoro los m\u00e1s sonados de Rep\u00fablica Dominicana|last=Rivera|first=Nayeli|publisher=Monitor Latino|language=spanish|accessdate=April 5, 2017}}\n*Colombia: {{cite web|url=http://charts.monitorlatino.com/top20/Colombia/General/20160815|title=Top 20 General Colombia: Del 15 al 21 de Agosto, 2016|publisher=Monitor Latino|language=Spanish|accessdate=August 18, 2017}}\n*Guatemala: {{cite web|url=http://charts.monitorlatino.com/top20/Guatemala/General/20161226|title=Top 20 General Guatemala: Del 26 de Diciembre 2016 al 1 de Enero 2017|publisher=Monitor Latino|language=Spanish|accessdate=August 18, 2017}}\n*Uruguay: {{cite web|url=http://charts.monitorlatino.com/top20/Uruguay/General/20170206|title=Top 20 General Uruguay: Del 6 al 12 de Febrero, 2017|publisher=Monitor Latino|language=Spanish|accessdate=August 18, 2017}}\n*Spain: {{cite web|url=http://www.promusicae.es/listas/semana/3286-canciones-semana-46-2016.pdf|title=Top 100 Canciones \u2013 SEMANA 46: del 11.11.2016 al 17.11.2016|publisher=promusicae.es|language=spanish|accessdate=November 24, 2016}}\n*Venezuela: {{cite web|url=http://national-report.com.ve/wp-content/uploads/TOP-100-DETECCIONES-SEMANAL-2.pdf|title=Top 100 Detecciones Semanal Semana 35 del 2016|publisher=national-report.com.ve|language=spanish|date=August 4, 2016|accessdate=October 20, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161101104148/http://national-report.com.ve/wp-content/uploads/TOP-100-DETECCIONES-SEMANAL-2.pdf|archive-date=November 1, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> It was certified 2\u00d7 platinum by the PROMUSICAE and the [[Argentine Chamber of Phonograms and Videograms Producers|CAPIF]], platinum by the IFPI Chile, and gold by the FIMI.<ref name=\"shakypromusicae\">{{cite web |url= http://www.elportaldemusica.es/cancion-12403-21873-daddy-yankee-shaky-shaky|title=Daddy Yankee \u2013 Shaky Shaky|publisher=elportaldemusica.es|accessdate=August 19, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"singles arg\">{{cite news|url= http://www.billboard.com.ar/noticia/2302/daddy-yankee-el-regreso-del-rey-del-reggaetn|title=Daddy Yankee: el regreso del rey del reggaet\u00f3n|work=Billboard Argentina|last=M\u00e1scolo|first=Santiago|language=Spanish|date=April 17, 2017|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"ifpichile\"/><ref name=\"fimishaky\">{{cite web |url= http://www.fimi.it/certificazioni#/category:singoli/year:2017/page:0/term:shaky_shaky|title=FIMI \u2013 Certificazioni \u2013 Shaky Shaky \u2013 Daddy Yankee|publisher=fimi.it|accessdate=April 8, 2017}}</ref>\n\n====Other releases====\n\"S\u00e1bado Rebelde\" was released as a promotional song on October 31, 2014. It features reggaeton duo [[Plan B (duo)|Plan B]] and was written by Daddy Yankee, Plan B, and the producer Haze. It peaked at number 49 on the US Hot Latin Songs chart on February 28, 2015.<ref name=\"hotlatin 4\">{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/300083/daddy-yankee/chart?page=3&f=363|title=Daddy Yankee \u2013 Chart history \u2013 Hot Latin Songs|work=Billboard|page=4|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\n\"Alerta Roja\" was released as a promotional song on Daddy Yankee's birthday on February 3, 2016 as a gift to his fans.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://peru.com/entretenimiento/musica/youtube-daddy-yankee-lanzo-su-tema-alerta-roja-15-artistas-noticia-437572|title=YouTube: Daddy Yankee lanz\u00f3 su tema \"Alerta Roja\" con 15 artistas|publisher=peru.com|language=spanish|date=February 4, 2016|accessdate=October 28, 2016}}</ref> The song's concept was to include some of the most popular Latin urban artists.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.telemundo.com/entretenimiento/2016/02/04/daddy-yankee-lanza-video-musical-alerta-roja-que-reune-15-artistas|title=Daddy Yankee lanza v\u00eddeo musical \"Alerta roja\" que re\u00fane a 15 artistas urbanos|language=Spanish|publisher=Telemundo|date=February 4, 2016|accessdate=August 19, 2016}}</ref> Singers [[Osmani Garc\u00eda]] and [[J \u00c1lvarez]] (Cuban and Puerto Rican, respectively) were originally guest artists but their verses were not included in the song. J \u00c1lvarez stated not knowing about being out of it and manifested his anger with Daddy Yankee through his social networks.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.rapeton.com/dejaron-fuera-j-alvarez-en-alerta-roja-pero-el-artista-montara-un-tema-nuevo/|title=Dejaron fuera a J Alvarez en \"Alerta Roja\" pero el artista montar\u00e1 un tema nuevo con los mismos versos|language=Spanish|publisher=rapeton.com|date=February 3, 2016|accessdate=August 24, 2016}}</ref> Two weeks later, \u00c1lvarez said that he was not aware of the song's concept and also that his anger was caused by a misunderstanding.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.primerahora.com/entretenimiento/farandula/nota/jalvarezreaccionaasuliocontranickyjamydaddyyankee-1137213/|title=J \u00c1lvarez reacciona a su l\u00edo contra Nicky Jam y Daddy Yankee|language=Spanish|publisher=primerahora.com|last=Brugueras|first=Melba|date=February 16, 2016|accessdate=August 24, 2016}}</ref>\n\n\"Otra Cosa\" was released as a [[Promotional recording#Promo single|promotional single]] on December 9, 2016 and features [[Natti Natasha]]. The song was released as the first single of [[Pina Records]]' upcoming studio album, ''La S\u00faper F\u00f3rmula'', but Daddy Yankee managed to also include it on ''El Disco Duro''.<ref name=\"Vernon\"/> The single peaked at number 21 on the US Hot Latin Songs chart on February 18, 2017 and at number 17 on Tropical Songs on January 14, 2017.<ref name=\"hotlatin 3\">{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/300083/daddy-yankee/chart?page=2&f=363|title=Daddy Yankee \u2013 Chart history \u2013 Hot Latin Songs|work=Billboard|page=3|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f[0]=ss_chart_search_title%3A%22Otra%20Cosa%22&f[1]=itm_field_chart_id%3A374&refine=1|title=''Billboard'' Chart Search \u2013 Otra Cosa \u2013 Daddy Yankee & Natti Natasha \u2013 Hot Latin Songs|work=Billboard|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> The song also peaked at number 50 in Venezuela.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://national-report.com.ve/top-100-semana-10-del-03032017-al-09032017/|title=Top 100 \u2013 Semana 10 del 03/03/2017 al 09/03/2017|publisher=national-report.com.ve|language=spanish|date=March 10, 2017|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref>\n\n\"La Rompe Corazones\" was released as a promotional single on January 6, 2017 as a gift from Daddy Yankee to his fans because of [[Epiphany (holiday)|Three Kings' Day]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://moda.com.pe/noticias/musica/daddy-yankee-ozuna-la-rompe-corazones-video-oficial-25686|title=Escucha lo nuevo de Daddy Yankee y Ozuna: 'La rompe corazones'|language=Spanish|publisher=moda.com.pe|date=January 6, 2017|accessdate=January 6, 2017}}</ref> The song peaked at number 12 on the US Hot Latin Songs chart on July 22, 2017.<ref name=\"Billboard\"/> Internationally, the single peaked at number 2 in Peru, at number 8 in Spain and Mexico, and at number 11 in Paraguay.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://charts.monitorlatino.com/top20/Peru/General/20170410|title=Top 20 General Per\u00fa: Del 10 al 16 de Abril, 2017|publisher=Monitor Latino|language=spanish|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.promusicae.es/listas/semana/3375-canciones-semana-11-2017.pdf|title=Top 100 Canciones \u2013 SEMANA 11: del 10.03.2017 al 16.03.2017|publisher=promusicae.es|language=spanish|accessdate=March 26, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://charts.monitorlatino.com/top20/Mexico/General/20170807|title=Top 20 General M\u00e9xico: Del 7 al 13 de Agosto, 2017|publisher=Monitor Latino|language=spanish|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://charts.monitorlatino.com/top20/Paraguay/General/20170724|title=Top 20 General Paraguay: Del 24 al 30 de Julio, 2017|publisher=Monitor Latino|language=spanish|accessdate=August 18, 2017}}</ref> It was certified 2\u00d7 platinum by the PROMUSICAE and gold by the CAPIF.<ref name=\"corazonespromusicae\">{{cite web |url= http://www.elportaldemusica.es/cancion-14008-24416-daddy-yankee-ozuna-la-rompe-corazones|title=Daddy Yankee / Ozuna \u2013 La Rompe Corazones|publisher=elportaldemusica.es|accessdate=March 16, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"singles arg\"/>\n\n\"Hula Hoop\" was released as a promotional single on March 3, 2017, originally recorded exclusively for Zumba fitness.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7710074/daddy-yankee-new-song-hula-hoop-zumba-listen|title=Daddy Yankee Delivers New Track 'Hula Hoop' in Partnership With Zumba|work=Billboard|last=Cantor-Navas|first=Judy|date=March 3, 2017|accessdate=August 19, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FU-_cDQMvL8|title=Daddy Yankee en directo en \"Anda Ya!\", 21 de Junio|quote=The song transcended beyond being a gift for zumba.|publisher=YouTube|language=Spanish|date=June 21, 2017|accessdate=August 19, 2017}} 0:15\u20131:05</ref> The song was based on the \"hula hoop\" hook from the remix of \"Shaky Shaky\" by Daddy Yankee, Nicky Jam and Plan B.<ref name=\"shaky new old\"/> It peaked at number 30 on the US Hot Latin Songs chart on March 25, 2017.<ref name=\"hotlatin 3\"/> Internationally, it reached number 9 in Chile, number 18 in Venezuela, number 20 in Colombia, and number 75 in Spain.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://charts.monitorlatino.com/top20/Chile/General/20170327|title=Top 20 General Chile: Del 27 de Marzo al 2 de Abril, 2017|publisher=Monitor Latino|language=Spanish|accessdate=August 18, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://national-report.com.ve/top-100-semana-16-del-14042017-al-20042017/|title=Top 100 \u2013 Semana 16 del 14/04/2017 al 20/04/2017|publisher=national-report.com.ve|language=spanish|date=April 21, 2017|accessdate=April 28, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://charts.monitorlatino.com/top20/Colombia/General/20170403|title=Top 20 General Colombia: Del 3 al 9 de Abril, 2017|publisher=Monitor Latino|language=spanish|accessdate=August 18, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.promusicae.es/listas/semana/3395-canciones-semana-15-2017.pdf |title=Top 100 Canciones \u2013 SEMANA 15: del 07.04.2017 al 13.04.2017|publisher=promusicae.es|language=spanish|accessdate=April 12, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Publication\n!Accolade\n!Recipient\n!Year\n!Rank\n!class=\"unsortable\"| {{Tooltip|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n|''[[IBT Media#Assets|Latin Times]]''\n|The 15 Most Addicting Latin Songs of 2015\n|\"S\u00edgueme y Te Sigo\"\n|2015\n|{{center|5}}\n|<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.latintimes.com/pulse/best-2015-15-most-addicting-latin-songs-were-all-rage-year-361670|title=Best Of 2015: 15 Most Addicting Latin Songs That Were All The Rage This Year!|publisher=Latin Times|last=Roiz|first=Jessica Luc\u00eda|date=December 27, 2015|accessdate=January 31, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[NBC News]]''\n|10 Top Latino Songs to Get You Moving\n|\"Shaky Shaky\"\n|2016\n|{{center|1}}\n|<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.nbcnews.com/news/latino/your-holiday-weekend-playlist-10-top-latino-songs-get-you-n686801|title=Your Holiday Weekend Playlist: 10 Top Latino Songs to Get You Moving|publisher=[[NBC News]]|last=Hernandez|first=Ericka|date=November 25, 2016|accessdate=January 31, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''\n|Best Latin Dance Songs of 2016\n|\"Shaky Shaky\"\n|2016\n|{{center|1}}\n|<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/events/year-in-music-2016/7616876/latin-dance-year-end-list-daddy-yankee-shakira|title=All We Want to Do Is Dance: Daddy Yankee, Shakira, Nicky Jam & More Latin Artists Who Got Fans Dancing in 2016|publisher=Billboard|last=Cobo|first=Leila|date=December 13, 2016|accessdate=January 31, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[PopSugar]]''\n|30 Songs That Pretty Much Defined Latin Music in 2016\n|\"Shaky Shaky\"\n|2016\n|{{center|19}}\n|<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.popsugar.com/latina/Best-Latin-Songs-2016-42692301?stream_view=1#photo-42692620|title=30 Songs That Pretty Much Defined Latin Music in 2016|publisher=[[PopSugar]]|last=Martin|first=Macy Daniela|date=December 31, 2016|accessdate=January 31, 2017}}</ref>\n|}\n\n\"S\u00edgueme y Te Sigo\" received a Latin American Music Award for Favorite Urban Song at the [[Latin American Music Awards of 2015|1st Latin American Music Awards]]. It was nominated for [[Latin Grammy Awards]] for [[Latin Grammy Award for Best Urban Song|Best Urban Song]] and [[Latin Grammy Award for Best Urban Performance|Best Urban Performance]] at the [[16th Annual Latin Grammy Awards|16th Latin Grammy Awards]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/6722629/latin-amas-2015-winners-list|title=Latin AMAs Winners List: Enrique Iglesias & Nicky Jam Win Big at Inaugural Awards Show|work=Billboard|last=Cobo|first=Leila|date=October 8, 2015|accessdate=April 29, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/events/latin-awards/6770030/latin-grammys-2015-winners-list|title=Latin Grammys 2015: See the Full Winners List|work=Billboard|date=November 19, 2015|accessdate=April 28, 2017}}</ref>\n\n\"Vaiv\u00e9n\" was nominated for an [[Winter Music Conference#Events|International Dance Music Award]] for Best Latin Dance Track at the 31st International Dance Music Awards and for a [[Lo Nuestro Award for Urban Song of the Year]] at the 29th Lo Nuestro Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wintermusicconference.com/events/idmas/index.php?wmcyear=2016#idmanominees|title=IDMA Winners for the year 2015 presented in 2016|publisher=[[Winter Music Conference]]|accessdate=April 29, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180828183706/http://wintermusicconference.com/events/idmas/index.php?wmcyear=2016#idmanominees|archive-date=August 28, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n\"Shaky Shaky\" received a [[Premios Juventud|Premio Juventud]] for Best Song for Dancing at the [[2017 Premios Juventud|14th Premios Juventud]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.univision.com/especiales/premios-juventud/estos-son-los-ganadores-de-los-premios-juventud-2017|title=Estos son los ganadores de los Premios Juventud 2017|trans-title=These are the winners for the Premios Juventud 2017|publisher=[[Univision]]|language=Spanish|date=July 6, 2017|accessdate=July 7, 2017}}</ref> It was nominated for [[Billboard Latin Music Awards|''Billboard'' Latin Music Awards]] for Hot Latin Song of the Year and Streaming Song of the Year at the 24th ''Billboard'' Latin Music Awards.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7678227/billboard-latin-music-awards-2017-see-the-full-list-of-finalists|title=Billboard Latin Music Awards 2017: See the Full List of Finalists |work=Billboard|last=Cobo|first=Leila|date=February 7, 2017|accessdate=February 12, 2017}}</ref> It also received a [[Billboard Music Award for Top Latin Song|Top Latin Song]] nomination at the [[2017 Billboard Music Awards|24th ''Billboard'' Music Awards]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/bbma/7752631/billboard-music-awards-2017-nominations-full-list|title=Drake, The Chainsmokers Lead Nominees for the 2017 Billboard Music Awards|work=Billboard|date=April 10, 2017|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\nTo be announced.\n\nThe following table is in order of release and is not the official track listing. Some songs may not appear on the final album.\n\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing = \n| extra_column = Producer(s)\n| title1 = S\u00e1bado Rebelde\n| note1 = featuring [[Plan B (duo)|Plan B]]\n| writer1 = {{hlist|Ram\u00f3n Ayala|Orlando Valle|Edwin V\u00e1zquez|Egbert Rosa}}\n| extra1 = {{hlist|Haze|Duran}}\n| length1 = 4:00\n| title2 = [[S\u00edgueme y Te Sigo]]\n| writer2 = {{hlist|R. Ayala|Carlos Ort\u00edz|Luis Ort\u00edz}}\n| extra2 = {{hlist|Chris Jeday|Gaby Music}}\n| length2 = 3:27\n| title3 = Vaiv\u00e9n\n| writer3 = {{hlist|R. Ayala|C. Ort\u00edz|L. Ort\u00edz}}\n| extra3 = {{hlist|Chris Jeday|Gaby Music}}\n| length3 = 3:45\n| title4 = Alerta Roja\n| note4 = featuring [[Zion & Lennox|Zion]], [[Nicky Jam]], [[Arc\u00e1ngel (singer)|Arc\u00e1ngel]], [[De La Ghetto]], Kafu Banton, [[Plan B (duo)|Plan B]], [[J Balvin]], [[Farruko]], [[Cosculluela]], El Micha, [[Brytiago]], Alexio, Mozart La Para, Secreto and [[Gente de Zona]]\n| writer4 = {{hlist|R. Ayala|Nick Rivera|Austin Santos|Rafael Castillo|Zico Garibaldi|O. Valle|E. V\u00e1zquez|Jos\u00e9 Osorio|Carlos Reyes|Jos\u00e9 Cosculluela|Michael Sierra|Bryan Santiago|Victor Rivera|Erickson Fernandez|Odalis P\u00e9rez|Alexander Delgado|Randy Mart\u00ednez}}\n| extra4 = {{hlist|Chris Jeday|Gaby Music|Jumbo}}\n| length4 = 10:23\n| title5 = [[Shaky Shaky]]\n| writer5 = {{hlist|R. Ayala|Urbani Mota|Luis Romero}}\n| extra5 = Los Evo Jedis\n| length5 = 3:52\n| title6 = [[Otra Cosa (Daddy Yankee song)|Otra Cosa]]\n| note6 = featuring [[Natti Natasha]]\n| writer6 = {{hlist|R. Ayala|Natalia Guti\u00e9rrez|E. Rosa}}\n| extra6 = Haze\n| length6 = 3:28\n| title7 = La Rompe Corazones\n| note7 = featuring Ozuna\n| writer7 = {{hlist|R. Ayala|Juan Carlos Ozuna|C. Ort\u00edz|Jes\u00fas Benitez}}\n| extra7 = {{hlist|Chris Jeday|Gaby Music}}\n| length7 = 3:19\n| title8 = C\u00f3digo de Amor\n| note8 = featuring [[Karol G]]; unreleased, announced in December 2015<ref>{{cite web |url= http://varietylatino.com/2016/musica/noticias/karol-g-entrevista-cantante-genero-urbano-nueva-cancion-casi-nada-daddy-yankee-230416/|title=Karol G nos habla del \u00e9xito de su nuevo sencillo y de lo que aprendi\u00f3 al colaborar con Daddy Yankee|publisher=varietylatino.com|language=spanish|date=April 1, 2016|accessdate=August 26, 2016}}</ref><ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RvjCQyFIR-I Preview of \"C\u00f3digo de Amor\", January 2016.]</ref>\n| writer8 = \n| extra8 = \n| length8 = \n| title9 = Tranque\n| note9 = featuring [[Lito & Polaco]]; unreleased, announced in February 2016<ref>[https://www.instagram.com/p/BBWdHQOrK3C/ Daddy Yankee and Lito MC Cassidy at a studio, February 2016.]</ref>\n| writer9 = \n| extra9 = \n| length9 = \n| title10 = Exagerao\n| note10 = featuring [[Zion & Lennox]]; unreleased, announced in March 2016<ref>[https://www.instagram.com/p/BDKuopLLK-l/ Daddy Yankee and Zion at The Hit Factory Criteria Miami, March 2016.]</ref>\n| writer10 = \n| extra10 = \n| length10 = \n| title11 = Percocet\n| note11 = Unreleased; announced in May 2016<ref>[https://www.instagram.com/p/BE2YRkArK0V/ Preview of \"Percocet\", May 2016.]</ref>\n| writer11 = \n| extra11 = \n| length11 = \n| title12 = Untitled track\n| note12 = featuring Brytiago; unreleased, announced in October 2016<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7QdRvDYGyM0 Brytiago: Backstage Con Maiky MT, October 2016.] From 19:46 to 20:15.</ref>\n| writer12 = \n| extra12 = \n| length12 = \n| title13 = Untitled [[bachat\u00f3n]] track\n| note13 = Unreleased; announced in October 2016<ref name=\"releasedate\"/>\n| writer13 = \n| extra13 = \n| length13 = \n| title14 = Auxilio\n| note14 = Unreleased; announced in October 2016<ref name=\"releasedate\"/>\n| writer14 = \n| extra14 = \n| length14 = \n| title15 = \n| note15 = \n| writer15 = \n| extra15 = \n| title16 = \n| length16 = \n| title17 = \n| length17 = \n| title18 = \n| length18 = \n| title19 = \n| length19 = \n| title20 = \n| length20 = \n| total_length = \n| length15 = \n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Daddy Yankee}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Disco Duro}}\n[[Category:Daddy Yankee albums]]\n[[Category:Spanish-language albums]]\n[[Category:Reggaeton albums]]\n[[Category:Upcoming albums]]\n[[Category:Sequel albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Studio album by Daddy Yankee}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = El Disco Duro\n| type       = Studio\n| artist     = [[Daddy Yankee]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = TBA\n| recorded   = Late 2014<ref name=\"Instagram\">{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/wL6WlQF6ux/|title=GRINDIN KING DADDY 2 ... 24 horas en el estudio y seguimos|publisher=Instagram|author1=Chris Jeday|author2=Daddy Yankee|type=Post|language=spanish|date=December 4, 2014|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref>\u2013 October 2016<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/BDoUxgoLK12/|title=No me hab\u00eda reportado, porque estamos enfocados. Siempre reaDY! Gracias por el apoyo incondicional, que siempre me brindan. KING DADDY (THE ALBUM)|author=Daddy Yankee|publisher=Instagram|type=Post|language=Spanish|date=March 31, 2016|accessdate=December 2, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/BEqB7vFLK2q/|title=#KingDaddy|author=Daddy Yankee|publisher=Instagram|type=Post|date=April 26, 2016|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref>\n| venue      =\n| studio     = {{Collapsible list|title=Various|titlestyle=font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;background:transparent;text-align:left\n{{Bulleted list|[[El Cartel Records]] <br /> {{small|([[Santurce, San Juan, Puerto Rico]])}}|[[Criteria Studios]]<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/BEvvYdWmXQX/|title=Daddy Yankee recording vocals at Criteria Studios' control room|publisher=instagram.com|date=April 28, 2016|accessdate=October 6, 2016}}</ref> <br />{{small|([[Miami]], [[Florida]], [[United States]]}})|Music Capos Studios<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/0oRuU_LK3A/|title=Daddy Yankee working on ''King Daddy II'' at Chris Jeday's Studio|publisher=instagram.com|language=spanish|date=March 24, 2015|accessdate=October 20, 2016}}</ref><br /> {{small|(San Juan, Puerto Rico)}}|Master House Studios<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/BCGM29Ul6q4/|title=Daddy Yankee and Chris Jeday working on ''King Daddy II'' at Master House Studios|publisher=instagram.com|date=February 22, 2016|accessdate=October 20, 2016}}</ref> <br />{{small|([[Doral, Florida]], United States)}}}}}}\n| genre      = [[Reggaeton]]\n| length     =\n| label      = [[El Cartel Records|El Cartel]]\n| producer   = {{hlist|Chris Jeday|Gaby Music|Jumbo|Los Evo Jedis}}\n| prev_title = [[El Imperio Nazza#El Imperio Nazza King Daddy Edition (2013)|King Daddy]]\n| prev_year  = 2013\n| year       = TBA\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = El Disco Duro\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[S\u00edgueme y Te Sigo]]\n | single1date = March 12, 2015\n | single2     = Vaiv\u00e9n\n | single2date = September 17, 2015\n | single3     = [[Shaky Shaky]]\n | single3date = April 8, 2016\n | single4     = [[Otra Cosa (Daddy Yankee song)|Otra Cosa]]\n | single4date = December 9, 2016\n | single5     = [[La Rompe Corazones]]\n | single5date = January 6, 2017\n | single6     = [[Vuelve (Daddy Yankee song)|Vuelve]]\n | single6date = September 29, 2017\n | single7     = [[Dura (song)|Dura]]\n | single7date = January 18, 2018\n | single8     = [[Hielo (song)|Hielo]]\n | single8date = May 18, 2018\n | single9     = Zum Zum\n | single9date = June 15, 2018\n | single10     = [[Adictiva]]\n | single10date = November 8, 2018\n | single11     = [[Con Calma]]\n | single11date = January 24, 2019\n | single12     = [[Si Supieras]]\n | single12date = June 28, 2019\n | single13     = [[Que Tire Pa Lante]]\n | single13date = October 18, 2019\n | single14     = Definitivamente\n | single14date = January 31, 2020\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''El Disco Duro''''' is the upcoming seventh studio album (fourteenth overall) by Puerto Rican rapper [[Daddy Yankee]], originally scheduled to be released during early 2017. Its original title was ''King Daddy II: Elemento DY'', a [[sequel]] to his previous album ''[[El Imperio Nazza#King Daddy Edition|King Daddy]]'', produced by Los De La Nazza, a production duo that worked with Daddy Yankee from 2007 to 2014. The album will include \"[[S\u00edgueme y Te Sigo]]\", \"Vaiv\u00e9n\" and \"[[Shaky Shaky]]\" as its singles, which were released between March 2015 and April 2016. Its release date is yet to be announced.\n\n==Background==\n[[File:DaddyYankee.jpg|thumb|left|Daddy Yankee in 2006.|150px]]\n''El Disco Duro'' (originally titled ''King Daddy II: Elemento DY'')<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.univision.com/puerto-rico/wkaq/daddy-yankee-se-encuentra-en-el-estudio-finalizando-su-proximo-album|title=Daddy Yankee se encuentra en el estudio finalizando su pr\u00f3ximo \u00e1lbum|trans-title=Daddy Yankee is in the studio finalizing his upcoming album|publisher=Univisi\u00f3n|language=Spanish|date=January 13, 2016|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.elnuevoherald.com/entretenimiento/musica/article47728830.html|title=Daddy Yankee y Don Omar se van al duelo para disputarse corona del reguet\u00f3n|work=[[El Nuevo Herald]]|language=Spanish|date=December 3, 2015|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> was going to be the sequel of his previous mixtape ''[[El Imperio Nazza#King Daddy Edition|King Daddy]]'', released in October 2013, which became the first digital-only Latin album that managed to rank within the top 10 on the US [[Top Latin Albums]] chart.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin-notas/5785843/inside-daddy-yankees-digital-only-king-album|title=Inside Daddy Yankee's Digital-Only 'King' Album|work=Billboard|date=November 11, 2013|last=Cobo|first=Leila|accessdate=August 20, 2016}}</ref> Two months after the release of ''King Daddy'', Daddy Yankee announced that there was going to be a physical version of the album, with exclusive bonus tracks, planned to be released during 2014, but it was not published after all.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.informador.com.mx/entretenimiento/2014/506146/6/daddy-yankee-lanzara-en-formato-fisico-el-album-king-daddy.htm|title=Daddy Yankee lanzar\u00e1 en formato f\u00edsico el \u00e1lbum 'King Daddy'|publisher=informador.com.mx|language=spanish|date=January 6, 2014|accessdate=October 28, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.elheraldo.hn/vida/600816-220/daddy-yankee-lanza-nuevo-disco-y-va-por-masm|title=Daddy Yankee lanza nuevo disco y va por m\u00e1s|work=El Heraldo|language=Spanish|date=April 7, 2014|accessdate=August 18, 2017|location=Honduras}}{{Dead link|date=December 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nThe Puerto Rican production duo [[Los de la Nazza]], which had been working with Daddy Yankee since 2007, left [[El Cartel Records]] and stopped being his main producers in order to focus on their careers. Chris Jeday and Gaby Music were hired as the album's main producers during late 2014. ''El Disco Duro'' was officially announced during mid-2014 as ''King Daddy II'' with the promotion of the single \"S\u00e1bado Rebelde\" featuring Puerto Rican duo [[Plan B (duo)|Plan B]], released on October 31.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.elnuevoherald.com/entretenimiento/musica/article16902242.html|title=Daddy Yankee sigue siendo el Rey|trans-title=Daddy Yankee is still the king|work=[[El Nuevo Herald]]|last=Vargas|first=Doraluz|language=Spanish|date=March 30, 2015|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn September 10, he was urgently moved to a nearby hospital in [[Cali]], [[Colombia]], where he was set to perform later that night. Daddy Yankee suffered a rise in blood pressure, [[hypoglycemia]] and dehydration, which almost caused him to suffer a heart attack before being treated by doctors. His condition improved and he was sent to rest in his native Puerto Rico, but had to cancel other concerts in Colombia.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.peopleenespanol.com/article/daddy-yankee-estuvo-al-borde-del-ataque-cardiaco|title=Daddy Yankee: los problemas de salud que le llevaron al hospital|publisher=peopleenespanol.com|last=Mabry Para\u00edso|first=Alexander|language=spanish|date=September 13, 2016|accessdate=October 17, 2016}}</ref> On October 19, he confirmed that his hypoglycemia worsened and turned into a [[prediabetes]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.elheraldo.hn/entretenimiento/1009872-466/reguetonero-daddy-yankee-confirma-grave-enfermedad|title=Reguetonero Daddy Yankee confirma grave enfermedad|publisher=eheraldo.hn|language=spanish|date=October 19, 2016|accessdate=October 20, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1953723-daddy-yankee-rompio-el-silencio-sobre-la-enfermedad-que-padecen-el-y-una-de-sus-hijas|title=Daddy Yankee rompi\u00f3 el silencio sobre la enfermedad que padecen \u00e9l y una de sus hijas|publisher=lanacion.com.ar|language=spanish|date=November 5, 2016|accessdate=November 6, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2017, he was featured on the reggaeton-pop single \"[[Despacito]]\" by Puerto Rican singer [[Luis Fonsi]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7669777/luis-fonsi-highest-debut-hot-latin-songs-chart|title=Luis Fonsi Earns His Highest Debut Ever on Hot Latin Songs Chart|work=Billboard|last=Mendizabal|first=Amaya|date=January 26, 2017|accessdate=February 26, 2017}}</ref> The song was a worldwide success, topping the charts of 45 countries, including a number 1 spot on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], the first for a primarily Spanish-language song since \"[[Macarena (song)|Macarena]]\" by [[Los del R\u00edo]] in 1996.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7793159/luis-fonsi-daddy-yankee-despacito-justin-bieber-number-one|title=Luis Fonsi & Daddy Yankee's 'Despacito' With Justin Bieber: No. 1 on the Billboard Hot 100 This Week|work=Billboard|first=Gary|last=Trust|date=May 15, 2017|accessdate=May 16, 2017}}</ref> The success of the song led Daddy Yankee to become the most listened artist worldwide on the streaming service [[Spotify]] on July 9, 2017, being the first Latin artist to do so.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/daddy-yankee-is-1-on-spotify-1st-latin-artist-to-do-so/2017/07/09/42a78bb2-64da-11e7-94ab-5b1f0ff459df_story.html|title=Daddy Yankee is #1 on Spotify; 1st Latin artist to do so|publisher=[[Washington Post]]|last=Ratner-Arias|first=Sigal|date=July 9, 2017|accessdate=July 9, 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170709221642/https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/daddy-yankee-is-1-on-spotify-1st-latin-artist-to-do-so/2017/07/09/42a78bb2-64da-11e7-94ab-5b1f0ff459df_story.html|archivedate=July 9, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.vibe.com/2017/07/daddy-yankee-number-1-spotify/|title=Daddy Yankee Breaks Barriers Becoming Top Streamed Artist On Spotify|publisher=[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]]|last=Pickens|first=Ashley|date=July 10, 2017|accessdate=July 10, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2017, Daddy Yankee announced a global partnership with [[Zumba|Zumba Fitness]], in which he would record exclusive tracks for the Zumba Instructor Network.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.vibe.com/2017/03/daddy-yankee-zumba-fitness-hula-hoop-dance/|title=Daddy Yankee Teams Up With Zumba For \"Hula Hoop\" Workout|publisher=[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]]|last=Imarenezor|first=Christine|date=March 8, 2017|accessdate=August 19, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://zlife.zumba.com/daddy-yankee-zumba-announce-global-partnership-support-artists-new-single-hula-hoop/|title=Daddy Yankee and Zumba Announce Global Partnership in Support of Artist\u2019s New Single \"Hula Hoop\"|publisher=zlife.zumba.com|date=March 3, 2017|accessdate=August 19, 2017}}</ref> On March 15, 2017, Daddy Yankee was recognized as Artist/Songwriter of the Year by the [[American Society of Composers, Authors and Publishers]] during the 25th Annual ASCAP Latin Music Awards.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7727807/daddy-yankee-joss-favela-ascap-latin-awards-winners|title=Daddy Yankee, Joss Favela Win Top Honors at ASCAP Latin Awards|work=Billboard|last=Cobo|first=Leila|date=March 15, 2017|accessdate=March 16, 2017}}</ref> A day later, he received a Puerto Rican Walk of Fame Star in San Juan, becoming the first urban act to do so.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.meridiano90.com/1829_eeuu/4402017_paseo-fama-de-puerto-rico-ya-cuenta-con-estrellas-a-reguetonero-y-deportistas.html|title=Paseo Fama de Puerto Rico ya cuenta con estrellas a reggaetonero y deportistas|publisher=meridiano90.com|language=Spanish|date=March 16, 2017|accessdate=March 16, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170317234007/http://www.meridiano90.com/1829_eeuu/4402017_paseo-fama-de-puerto-rico-ya-cuenta-con-estrellas-a-reguetonero-y-deportistas.html|archive-date=March 17, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7728541/daddy-yankee-ednita-nazario-honored-puerto-rico|title=Daddy Yankee & Ednita Nazario Honored by the Puerto Rico Hall of Fame|work=Billboard|last=Fernandez|first=Suzette|date=March 17, 2017|accessdate=March 19, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\n\"[[S\u00edgueme y Te Sigo]]\" is a dance love song written by Daddy Yankee, Chris Jeday and Luis \"Wichi\" Ort\u00edz Rivera, inspired by [[social networks]] but not centred on them, and mixes reggaeton with Latin pop, including an electric guitar riff.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vivelohoy.com/entretenimiento/8446109/video-sigueme-y-te-sigo-de-daddy-yankee|title=S\u00edgueme Y Te Sigo, de Daddy Yankee|publisher=vivelohoy.com|language=spanish|date=May 11, 2015|accessdate=August 19, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160827152720/http://www.vivelohoy.com/entretenimiento/8446109/video-sigueme-y-te-sigo-de-daddy-yankee|archive-date=August 27, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n\"Vaiv\u00e9n\" is a [[moombahton]] song written by Daddy Yankee, Luis \"Wichi\" Ort\u00edz Rivera and the producer Chris Jeday.\n\n\"[[Shaky Shaky]]\" is a reggaeton song born as a [[Freestyle rap|freestyle]] during early December 2015, and was later recorded by the production duo Los Evo Jedis.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.primerahora.com/entretenimiento/farandula/nota/daddyyankeecompartesushakyshaky-1147337/|title=Daddy Yankee comparte su \"Shaky Shaky\"|publisher=primerahora.com|language=Spanish|date=April 11, 2016|accessdate=August 20, 2016}}</ref> According to Daddy Yankee, the main vocals were recorded in one take and the song musically mixes sounds from old and new school reggaeton.<ref name=\"shaky\">{{cite web |url= http://www.latintimes.com/daddy-yankee-shaky-shaky-premiere-5-reasons-why-you-have-watch-el-cangri-music-video-392998|title=Daddy Yankee 'Shaky Shaky' Premiere: 5 Reasons Why You Have To Watch 'El Cangri' Music Video|publisher=Latin Times|last=Valdez|first=Maria|date=July 15, 2016|accessdate=August 22, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"shaky new old\">{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7556771/daddy-yankee-shaky-shaky-number-1-hot-latin-songs-chart|title=Daddy Yankee Celebrates 'Shaky Shaky' Hitting No. 1 on Hot Latin Songs Chart|last=Mendizabal|first=Amaya|work=Billboard|date=October 25, 2016|accessdate=October 25, 2016}}</ref> The [[keyboard bass]] line was based on the one from the single \"Murder She Wrote\" by [[Chaka Demus & Pliers]], released in 1992.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.nytimes.com/2016/09/03/arts/music/playlist-young-thug-cherry-glazerr-sylvan-esso.html|title=The Playlist: Young Thug Turns the Summer's Big Meme Into a Standout Track|publisher=nytimes.com|last1=Pareles|first1=Jon|last2=Caramanica|first2=Jon|last3=Chinen|first3=Nate|date=September 2, 2016|accessdate=September 14, 2016}}</ref> It also includes a repeating sample of a horse's neigh from [[Mel and Tim]]'s \"Good Guys Only Win in the Movies\" (1970), which became popular after [[Cypress Hill]]'s \"[[Insane in the Brain]]\" (1993).<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.whosampled.com/sample/854/Cypress-Hill-Insane-in-the-Brain-Mel-%26-Tim-Good-Guys-Only-Win-in-the-Movies/|title=Cypress Hill's 'Insane in the Brain' sample of Mel & Tim's 'Good Guys Only Win in the Movies'|publisher=whosampled.com|accessdate=October 25, 2016}}</ref>\n\n\"Otra Cosa\" features Dominican singer [[Natti Natasha]] and is a fusion between reggaeton, dancehall and moombahton music written by Daddy Yankee, Natti Natasha and Puerto Rican producer Haze.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.univision.com/noticias/edicion-digital/daddy-yankee-y-natti-natasha-estrenan-otra-cosa-su-cancion-para-ponerle-ritmo-al-fin-de-ano-video|title=Daddy Yankee y Natti Natasha estrenan \u2018Otra cosa\u2019, su canci\u00f3n para ponerle ritmo al fin de a\u00f1o|publisher=Univisi\u00f3n|language=Spanish|date=December 8, 2016|accessdate=August 17, 2017}} 1:20\u20131:40</ref><ref name=\"otra cosa int\">{{cite web |url= https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Aaibwc0jF6w|title=Entrevista a Daddy Yankee y Dominicana Natti Natasha|type=Video|publisher=YouTube|language=Spanish|date=January 26, 2017|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> The lyrics are about [[lovesickness]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.diariolasamericas.com/cultura/daddy-yankee-y-natti-natasha-estrenan-videoclip-otra-cosa-n4113444|title=Daddy Yankee y Natti Natasha estrenan videoclip de \"Otra cosa\"|trans-title=Daddy Yankee and Natti Natasha premiere \"Otra Cosa\" video clip|work=[[Diario Las Am\u00e9ricas]]|language=Spanish|date=January 27, 2017|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> The concept of the song was brought to Daddy Yankee by Haze and Natti Natasha in order to be included on the track listing of ''La Super F\u00f3rmula'', a [[Pina Records]] studio album by various artists.<ref name=\"otra cosa int\"/><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.metro.pr/pr/entretener/2016/12/09/daddy-yankee-natti-natasha-lanzan-otra-cosa.html|title=Daddy Yankee y Natti Natasha lanzan \"Otra cosa\"|publisher=metro.pr|language=Spanish|date=December 9, 2016|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\n\"La Rompe Corazones\" features Puerto Rican singer Ozuna and was written by Daddy Yankee, Ozuna, Chris Jeday and Puerto Rican songwriter Jes\u00fas \"Benny Benni\" Benitez Hiraldo.<ref name=\"Billboard\">{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f[0]=ss_chart_search_title%3A%22La%20Rompe%20Corazones%22&f[1]=itm_field_chart_id%3A363&refine=1|title=''Billboard'' Chart Search \u2013 La Rompe Corazones \u2013 Daddy Yankee X Ozuna \u2013 Hot Latin Songs|work=Billboard|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> The song tells the story of a lovesick woman who no longer trusts her relationships, taking revenge on other men through her frustration.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.daddyyankee.com/master-76|title=Daddy Yankee habla qu\u00e9 lo inspir\u00f3 en La Rompe Corazones|publisher=daddyyankee.com|date=January 11, 2017|accessdate=January 13, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\n[[File:North Miami FL Criteria Studios01.jpg|thumb|right|[[Criteria Studios]] was one of various studios the album was recorded at.|220px]]\nThe first known recording session for ''El Disco Duro'' with producers Chris Jeday and Gaby Music was held in December 2014.<ref name=\"Instagram\">{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/wL6WlQF6ux/|title=GRINDIN KING DADDY 2 ... 24 horas en el estudio y seguimos|publisher=Instagram|author1=Chris Jeday|author2=Daddy Yankee|type=Post|language=spanish|date=December 4, 2014|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref> The last known session was carried out in May 2017 with the recording of the track \"Percocet\".<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/BE2YRkArK0V/|title=El tema controversial del album: \"PERCOCET\"|publisher=Instagram|author=Daddy Yankee|type=Post|language=Spanish|date=May 1, 2016|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/BE3EdLBl6s4/|title=Dandole \ud83d\udc8a\ud83d\udc8a PERCOCET \ud83d\udc8a\ud83d\udc8a\ud83c\udfbc\ud83c\udfbc @daddyyankee @gabymusic la musa a 100|publisher=Instagram|author=Chris Jeday|type=Post|language=Spanish|date=May 1, 2016|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> The recording was resumed during mid-October 2016 with Daddy Yankee and Dominican singer [[Natti Natasha]] recording the single \"Otra Cosa\" for [[Pina Records]]' upcoming studio album ''La Super F\u00f3rmula''.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/BLe-HAwhh2n/|title=Trabajando con la baby @nattinatasha \ud83d\ude18\ud83c\udf39\ud83c\udf39@pinarecords1|publisher=Instagram|author=Daddy Yankee|type=Post|language=spanish|date=October 12, 2016|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> However, Daddy Yankee managed to include the track on ''El Disco Duro'' during December 2016.<ref name=\"Vernon\">{{cite web |url= http://www.univision.com/musica/reggaeton/exclusiva-todo-sobre-otra-cosa-la-nueva-cancion-de-daddy-yankee-y-natti-natasha|title=Exclusiva: Todo sobre 'Otra cosa', la nueva canci\u00f3n de Daddy Yankee y Natti Natasha|language=Spanish|publisher=Univisi\u00f3n|last=Vernon|first=Beatriz|date=December 7, 2016|accessdate=December 14, 2016}}</ref> On February 21, 2017, Daddy Yankee uploaded an image on his official [[Instagram]] account listening to the album.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/BQy4NEwgLLx/|title=Studio \ud83c\udfa7.. Escuchando\ud83d\udc42\ud83c\udffc EL DISCO DURO \ud83d\udcc0\ud83d\udcbf\ud83d\udcc0\ud83d\udcbf\ud83d\udcc0|publisher=Instagram|author=Daddy Yankee|type=Post|language=spanish|date=February 21, 2017|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\nStudios where the album was recorded includes Daddy Yankee's El Cartel Studios in [[Santurce, San Juan, Puerto Rico]], Chris Jeday's Music Capos Studios in Puerto Rico, [[Criteria Studios]] in [[Miami, Florida, USA]], and Master House Studios in [[Doral, Florida|Doral, Florida, USA]].<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/BEvvYdWmXQX/|title=There's fire in Studio D ~courtesy of Daddy Yankee. \u2668\ufe0f Some artists like to record vocals in the control room DY is one of them!|publisher=Instagram|author=Criteria Recording Studios|type=Post|date=April 28, 2016|accessdate=October 6, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/BCGM29Ul6q4/|title=Kd2 @daddyyankee|publisher=Instagram|author=Chris Jeday|type=Post|date=February 22, 2016|accessdate=October 20, 2016}}</ref>\n\n\"S\u00edgueme y Te Sigo\" was mixed at El Cartel Studios in February 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/zPycZPF6m3/|title=MUSIC CAPOS $$$ MIXING SECTION WITH @earcandypro @daddyyankee SIGUEME Y TE SIGO|publisher=Instagram|author=Chris Jeday|type=Post|language=spanish|date=February 18, 2015|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/zMvKxmF6pR/|title=Laborando con @daddyyankee @gabymusic y @earcandypro -TEMA SIGUEME Y TE SIGO|publisher=Instagram|author=Chris Jeday|type=Post|language=spanish|date=February 17, 2015|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/ykkh-WF6in/|title=Tema: \"SIGUEME Y TE SIGO\" #KD \u264a\ufe0f. Bastagazo!! HIT!. Que pensaban que na' m\u00e1s estaba puesto pa' la calle? No confundan mi hobby con mi NEGOCIO. Atte. EL QUE SIEMPRE LES CAMBIA EL JUEGO! @daddyyankee @chrisjeday @gabymusic|publisher=Instagram|author=Daddy Yankee|type=Post|language=spanish|date=February 1, 2015|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> Sound test for \"Vaiv\u00e9n\" was held by Chris Jeday at Music Capos Studios during early August 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/6bF5xxwSkG/|title=VAIVEN PRUEBA DE SONIDO DONDE TODO COMIENZA \ud83c\udfb9\ud83c\udfb9\ud83c\udfbc\ud83c\udfbc CREANDO MUSIC CAPOS @daddyyankee @gabymusic WORLDWIDE SOUND|publisher=Instagram|author=Chris Jeday|type=Post|language=spanish|date=August 15, 2015|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> The song was later mixed at Criteria Studios and at El Cartel Studios the same month.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/63c1hrl6qX/|title=SIEMPRE BUSCANDO LA PERFECCION MIXING SESSION #ELVAIVEN DY @daddyyankee EN LOS CONTROLES LOS DUROS @earcandypro @gabymusic MUSIC CAPOS #ELVAIVEN WORLDWIDE SOUND|publisher=Instagram|author=Chris Jeday|type=Post|language=spanish|date=August 26, 2015|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.instagram.com/p/61U8fWF6qJ/|title=MIXING #ELVAIVEN CON @daddyyankee y @gabymusic CARTEL|publisher=Instagram|author=Chris Jeday|type=Post|language=spanish|date=August 26, 2015|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\nDaddy Yankee confirmed on October 26, 2016 during a meeting with Zumba fitness creator [[Beto Perez]] at [[Pina Records]] that ''El Disco Duro'' will be released during early 2017, most likely during January or February.<ref name=\"releasedate\">{{cite web |url= http://www.univision.com/musica/reggaeton/daddy-yankee-dio-un-adelanto-de-su-nuevo-disco-al-fundador-de-zumba|title=Daddy Yankee dio un adelanto de su nuevo disco al fundador de Zumba|publisher=Univisi\u00f3n|language=spanish|last=Miserachi|first=Raquel|date=October 26, 2016|accessdate=October 27, 2016}}</ref> On June 21, 2017, Daddy Yankee stated that he postponed the album's release due to finding more successful the release of singles instead of an entire record.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FU-_cDQMvL8|title=Daddy Yankee en directo en \"Anda Ya!\", 21 de Junio|quote=I was going to release the album but for some reason single after single is working better.|publisher=YouTube|language=Spanish|date=June 21, 2017|accessdate=August 19, 2017}} 17:33\u201318:06</ref> In December 2014, ''Billboard'' magazine added digital and streaming information to count sales: 1,000 digital songs sales and 1,500 song streams separately equal one album sale, which may affect the chart placement of the album. Considered on-demand audio services includes [[Spotify]], [[Google Play]], [[Beats Music]] and [[Xbox Music]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6320099/billboard-200-makeover-streams-digital-tracks|title=Billboard 200 Makeover: Album Chart to Incorporate Streams & Track Sales|work=Billboard|date=November 19, 2014|accessdate=November 3, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Singles===\n{{Listen\n|filename=Daddy Yankee - Shaky Shaky.ogg\n|title=\"Shaky Shaky\"\n|description=A 29-second sample of \"[[Shaky Shaky]]\". The song blends sounds from old and new school reggaeton. It became a number-one hit single on the US Latin and Tropical Songs charts.\n|format=[[Ogg]]}}\n\n\"[[S\u00edgueme y Te Sigo]]\" was released as the first single on March 12, 2015. It peaked at number 6 on the US [[Hot Latin Songs]] chart on June 13, 2015 and at number 5 on [[Tropical Songs]] on April 18, 2015.<ref name=\"hotlatin 2\">{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/300083/daddy-yankee/chart?page=1&f=363|title=Daddy Yankee \u2013 Chart history \u2013 Hot Latin Songs|work=Billboard|page=2|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"tropical 1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/300083/daddy-yankee/chart?f=340|title=Daddy Yankee \u2013 Chart history \u2013 Tropical Songs|work=Billboard|page=1|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> Internationally, the song peaked at number 12 in Spain, at number 32 in Venezuela, and at number 198 in France.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.promusicae.es/listas/semana/2923-canciones-semana-28-2015.pdf |title=Top 100 Canciones \u2013 SEMANA 28: del 06.07.2015 al 09.07.2015  |publisher=promusicae.es|language=spanish|accessdate=August 26, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"siguemevaiven\">{{cite web|url=http://national-report.com.ve/wp-content/uploads/TOP-100-DETECCIONES-SEMANAL-31.pdf|title=Top 100 Detecciones Semanal Semana 31 del 2016|publisher=national-report.com.ve|language=spanish|date=September 1, 2016|accessdate=October 21, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161101104544/http://national-report.com.ve/wp-content/uploads/TOP-100-DETECCIONES-SEMANAL-31.pdf|archive-date=November 1, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.snepmusique.com/tops-semaine/top-singles-telecharges/?ye=2015&we=28 |title=Le Top de la semaine : Top Singles T\u00e9l\u00e9charg\u00e9s \u2013 Semaine du Aout 14, 2015 |publisher=snepmusique.com|language=french|date=August 14, 2015|accessdate=August 26, 2016}}</ref> It was certified 2\u00d7 platinum by the [[PROMUSICAE]], platinum by the IFPI Chile, and gold by the [[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana|FIMI]].<ref name=\"siguemepromusicae\">{{cite web |url= http://www.elportaldemusica.es/cancion-10039-18054-daddy-yankee-sigueme-y-te-sigo|title=Daddy Yankee \u2013 S\u00edgueme y Te Sigo|publisher=elportaldemusica.es|accessdate=August 19, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"ifpichile\">{{cite web|url=http://www.daddyyankee.com/master-71|title=Chile Recibe al Rey del Reggaeton con Triple Disco de Platino por sus sencillos ''Shaky Shaky'', ''S\u00edgueme y Te Sigo'' y ''Vaiv\u00e9n''|publisher=daddyyankee.com|language=spanish|date=November 29, 2016|accessdate=November 29, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161220073558/http://www.daddyyankee.com/master-71|archive-date=December 20, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"shakyfimi\">{{cite web |url= http://www.fimi.it/certificazioni#/category:tutte/year:2016/page:0/term:Daddy|title=Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana \u2013 Certificazioni \u2013 Daddy Yankee  2016|publisher=fimi.it|language=italian|accessdate=January 23, 2017}}</ref>\n\n\"Vaiv\u00e9n\" was released as the second single on September 17, 2015. Although the song does not have an official music video, it managed to peak at number 7 on the US Hot Latin Songs chart and at number 3 on Tropical Songs, both on January 23, 2016.<ref name=\"hotlatin 2\"/><ref name=\"tropical 1\"/> Internationally, the single reached number 19 in Spain and number 34 in Venezuela.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.promusicae.es/listas/semana/3003-canciones-semana-43-2015.pdf|title=Top 100 Canciones \u2013 SEMANA 43: del 16.10.2015 al 22.10.2015  |publisher=promusicae.es|language=spanish|accessdate=August 26, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"siguemevaiven\"/> It received a platinum certification by the PROMUSICAE and the IFPI Chile.<ref name=\"vaivenpromusicae\">{{cite web |url= http://www.elportaldemusica.es/cancion-11030-19571-daddy-yankee-vaiven|title=Daddy Yankee \u2013 Vaiv\u00e9n|publisher=elportaldemusica.es|accessdate=August 19, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"ifpichile\"/>\n\n\"[[Shaky Shaky]]\" was released as the third single on April 8, 2016, although it was originally planned as a gift from Yankee to his fans for 2015 Christmas. The song reached the number 1 spot on the US Hot Latin Songs and [[Tropical Songs]] charts on November 5 and August 20, 2016, respectively.<ref name=\"hotlatin 1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/300083/daddy-yankee/chart?f=363|title=Daddy Yankee \u2013 Chart history \u2013 Hot Latin Songs|work=Billboard|page=1|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"tropical 1\"/> It became his fourth No. 1 song on the Hot Latin Songs chart and his first one since February 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7556711/daddy-yankee-hot-latin-songs-shaky-shaky|title=Hitting No. 1, Daddy Yankee Style: Listen to His 4 Biggest Chart Hits|work=Billboard|last=Fernandez|first=Suzette|date=October 25, 2016|accessdate=October 25, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"hotlatin 1\"/> It also peaked at number 88 in the [[Billboard Hot 100|United States]], becoming Daddy Yankee's first entry on the Hot 100 since the debut of \"[[Impacto]]\" on May 26, 2007.<ref name=\"hot100\">{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/300083/daddy-yankee/chart?f=379|title=Daddy Yankee \u2013 Chart history \u2013 The Hot 100|work=Billboard|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100/2007-05-26|title=The Hot 100 \u2013 Week of May 26, 2007|work=Billboard|date=May 26, 2007|accessdate=January 15, 2017}}</ref> Internationally, the song peaked at number 1 in Mexico and the Dominican Republic, at number 4 in Colombia, at number 11 in Guatemala, at number 14 in Uruguay, at number 25 in Spain, and at number 42 in Venezuela.<ref>International peaks for \"Shaky Shaky\":\n*M\u00e9xico: {{cite web|url=http://monitorlatino.com/shaky-shaky-sobre-mi-como-no-queriendo-y-let-me-love-you-las-canciones-con-mas-audiencia-en-mexico/|title=\"Shaky, shaky\", \"Sobre m\u00ed\", \"Como no queriendo\" y \"Let me love you\" las canciones con m\u00e1s audiencia en M\u00e9xico|last=Rivera|first=Nayeli|publisher=Monitor Latino|language=spanish|date=October 3, 2016|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}\n*Dominican Republic: {{cite web|url=http://monitorlatino.com/daddy-yankee-anthony-santos-jose-montoro-los-mas-sonados-de-republica-dominicana/|title=Daddy Yankee, Anthony Santos, Jos\u00e9 Montoro los m\u00e1s sonados de Rep\u00fablica Dominicana|last=Rivera|first=Nayeli|publisher=Monitor Latino|language=spanish|accessdate=April 5, 2017}}\n*Colombia: {{cite web|url=http://charts.monitorlatino.com/top20/Colombia/General/20160815|title=Top 20 General Colombia: Del 15 al 21 de Agosto, 2016|publisher=Monitor Latino|language=Spanish|accessdate=August 18, 2017}}\n*Guatemala: {{cite web|url=http://charts.monitorlatino.com/top20/Guatemala/General/20161226|title=Top 20 General Guatemala: Del 26 de Diciembre 2016 al 1 de Enero 2017|publisher=Monitor Latino|language=Spanish|accessdate=August 18, 2017}}\n*Uruguay: {{cite web|url=http://charts.monitorlatino.com/top20/Uruguay/General/20170206|title=Top 20 General Uruguay: Del 6 al 12 de Febrero, 2017|publisher=Monitor Latino|language=Spanish|accessdate=August 18, 2017}}\n*Spain: {{cite web|url=http://www.promusicae.es/listas/semana/3286-canciones-semana-46-2016.pdf|title=Top 100 Canciones \u2013 SEMANA 46: del 11.11.2016 al 17.11.2016|publisher=promusicae.es|language=spanish|accessdate=November 24, 2016}}\n*Venezuela: {{cite web|url=http://national-report.com.ve/wp-content/uploads/TOP-100-DETECCIONES-SEMANAL-2.pdf|title=Top 100 Detecciones Semanal Semana 35 del 2016|publisher=national-report.com.ve|language=spanish|date=August 4, 2016|accessdate=October 20, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161101104148/http://national-report.com.ve/wp-content/uploads/TOP-100-DETECCIONES-SEMANAL-2.pdf|archive-date=November 1, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> It was certified 2\u00d7 platinum by the PROMUSICAE and the [[Argentine Chamber of Phonograms and Videograms Producers|CAPIF]], platinum by the IFPI Chile, and gold by the FIMI.<ref name=\"shakypromusicae\">{{cite web |url= http://www.elportaldemusica.es/cancion-12403-21873-daddy-yankee-shaky-shaky|title=Daddy Yankee \u2013 Shaky Shaky|publisher=elportaldemusica.es|accessdate=August 19, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"singles arg\">{{cite news|url= http://www.billboard.com.ar/noticia/2302/daddy-yankee-el-regreso-del-rey-del-reggaetn|title=Daddy Yankee: el regreso del rey del reggaet\u00f3n|work=Billboard Argentina|last=M\u00e1scolo|first=Santiago|language=Spanish|date=April 17, 2017|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"ifpichile\"/><ref name=\"fimishaky\">{{cite web |url= http://www.fimi.it/certificazioni#/category:singoli/year:2017/page:0/term:shaky_shaky|title=FIMI \u2013 Certificazioni \u2013 Shaky Shaky \u2013 Daddy Yankee|publisher=fimi.it|accessdate=April 8, 2017}}</ref>\n\n====Other releases====\n\"S\u00e1bado Rebelde\" was released as a promotional song on October 31, 2014. It features reggaeton duo [[Plan B (duo)|Plan B]] and was written by Daddy Yankee, Plan B, and the producer Haze. It peaked at number 49 on the US Hot Latin Songs chart on February 28, 2015.<ref name=\"hotlatin 4\">{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/300083/daddy-yankee/chart?page=3&f=363|title=Daddy Yankee \u2013 Chart history \u2013 Hot Latin Songs|work=Billboard|page=4|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\n\"Alerta Roja\" was released as a promotional song on Daddy Yankee's birthday on February 3, 2016 as a gift to his fans.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://peru.com/entretenimiento/musica/youtube-daddy-yankee-lanzo-su-tema-alerta-roja-15-artistas-noticia-437572|title=YouTube: Daddy Yankee lanz\u00f3 su tema \"Alerta Roja\" con 15 artistas|publisher=peru.com|language=spanish|date=February 4, 2016|accessdate=October 28, 2016}}</ref> The song's concept was to include some of the most popular Latin urban artists.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.telemundo.com/entretenimiento/2016/02/04/daddy-yankee-lanza-video-musical-alerta-roja-que-reune-15-artistas|title=Daddy Yankee lanza v\u00eddeo musical \"Alerta roja\" que re\u00fane a 15 artistas urbanos|language=Spanish|publisher=Telemundo|date=February 4, 2016|accessdate=August 19, 2016}}</ref> Singers [[Osmani Garc\u00eda]] and [[J \u00c1lvarez]] (Cuban and Puerto Rican, respectively) were originally guest artists but their verses were not included in the song. J \u00c1lvarez stated not knowing about being out of it and manifestated his anger with Daddy Yankee through his social networks.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.rapeton.com/dejaron-fuera-j-alvarez-en-alerta-roja-pero-el-artista-montara-un-tema-nuevo/|title=Dejaron fuera a J Alvarez en \"Alerta Roja\" pero el artista montar\u00e1 un tema nuevo con los mismos versos|language=Spanish|publisher=rapeton.com|date=February 3, 2016|accessdate=August 24, 2016}}</ref> Two weeks later, \u00c1lvarez said that he was not aware of the song's concept and also that his anger was caused by a misunderstanding.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.primerahora.com/entretenimiento/farandula/nota/jalvarezreaccionaasuliocontranickyjamydaddyyankee-1137213/|title=J \u00c1lvarez reacciona a su l\u00edo contra Nicky Jam y Daddy Yankee|language=Spanish|publisher=primerahora.com|last=Brugueras|first=Melba|date=February 16, 2016|accessdate=August 24, 2016}}</ref>\n\n\"Otra Cosa\" was released as a [[Promotional recording#Promo single|promotional single]] on December 9, 2016 and features [[Natti Natasha]]. The song was released as the first single of [[Pina Records]]' upcoming studio album, ''La S\u00faper F\u00f3rmula'', but Daddy Yankee managed to also include it on ''El Disco Duro''.<ref name=\"Vernon\"/> The single peaked at number 21 on the US Hot Latin Songs chart on February 18, 2017 and at number 17 on Tropical Songs on January 14, 2017.<ref name=\"hotlatin 3\">{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/300083/daddy-yankee/chart?page=2&f=363|title=Daddy Yankee \u2013 Chart history \u2013 Hot Latin Songs|work=Billboard|page=3|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f[0]=ss_chart_search_title%3A%22Otra%20Cosa%22&f[1]=itm_field_chart_id%3A374&refine=1|title=''Billboard'' Chart Search \u2013 Otra Cosa \u2013 Daddy Yankee & Natti Natasha \u2013 Hot Latin Songs|work=Billboard|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> The song also peaked at number 50 in Venezuela.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://national-report.com.ve/top-100-semana-10-del-03032017-al-09032017/|title=Top 100 \u2013 Semana 10 del 03/03/2017 al 09/03/2017|publisher=national-report.com.ve|language=spanish|date=March 10, 2017|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref>\n\n\"La Rompe Corazones\" was released as a promotional single on January 6, 2017 as a gift from Daddy Yankee to his fans because of [[Epiphany (holiday)|Three Kings' Day]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://moda.com.pe/noticias/musica/daddy-yankee-ozuna-la-rompe-corazones-video-oficial-25686|title=Escucha lo nuevo de Daddy Yankee y Ozuna: 'La rompe corazones'|language=Spanish|publisher=moda.com.pe|date=January 6, 2017|accessdate=January 6, 2017}}</ref> The song peaked at number 12 on the US Hot Latin Songs chart on July 22, 2017.<ref name=\"Billboard\"/> Internationally, the single peaked at number 2 in Peru, at number 8 in Spain and Mexico, and at number 11 in Paraguay.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://charts.monitorlatino.com/top20/Peru/General/20170410|title=Top 20 General Per\u00fa: Del 10 al 16 de Abril, 2017|publisher=Monitor Latino|language=spanish|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.promusicae.es/listas/semana/3375-canciones-semana-11-2017.pdf|title=Top 100 Canciones \u2013 SEMANA 11: del 10.03.2017 al 16.03.2017|publisher=promusicae.es|language=spanish|accessdate=March 26, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://charts.monitorlatino.com/top20/Mexico/General/20170807|title=Top 20 General M\u00e9xico: Del 7 al 13 de Agosto, 2017|publisher=Monitor Latino|language=spanish|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://charts.monitorlatino.com/top20/Paraguay/General/20170724|title=Top 20 General Paraguay: Del 24 al 30 de Julio, 2017|publisher=Monitor Latino|language=spanish|accessdate=August 18, 2017}}</ref> It was certified 2\u00d7 platinum by the PROMUSICAE and gold by the CAPIF.<ref name=\"corazonespromusicae\">{{cite web |url= http://www.elportaldemusica.es/cancion-14008-24416-daddy-yankee-ozuna-la-rompe-corazones|title=Daddy Yankee / Ozuna \u2013 La Rompe Corazones|publisher=elportaldemusica.es|accessdate=March 16, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"singles arg\"/>\n\n\"Hula Hoop\" was released as a promotional single on March 3, 2017, originally recorded exclusively for Zumba fitness.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7710074/daddy-yankee-new-song-hula-hoop-zumba-listen|title=Daddy Yankee Delivers New Track 'Hula Hoop' in Partnership With Zumba|work=Billboard|last=Cantor-Navas|first=Judy|date=March 3, 2017|accessdate=August 19, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FU-_cDQMvL8|title=Daddy Yankee en directo en \"Anda Ya!\", 21 de Junio|quote=The song transcended beyond being a gift for zumba.|publisher=YouTube|language=Spanish|date=June 21, 2017|accessdate=August 19, 2017}} 0:15\u20131:05</ref> The song was based on the \"hula hoop\" hook from the remix of \"Shaky Shaky\" by Daddy Yankee, Nicky Jam and Plan B.<ref name=\"shaky new old\"/> It peaked at number 30 on the US Hot Latin Songs chart on March 25, 2017.<ref name=\"hotlatin 3\"/> Internationally, it reached number 9 in Chile, number 18 in Venezuela, number 20 in Colombia, and number 75 in Spain.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://charts.monitorlatino.com/top20/Chile/General/20170327|title=Top 20 General Chile: Del 27 de Marzo al 2 de Abril, 2017|publisher=Monitor Latino|language=Spanish|accessdate=August 18, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://national-report.com.ve/top-100-semana-16-del-14042017-al-20042017/|title=Top 100 \u2013 Semana 16 del 14/04/2017 al 20/04/2017|publisher=national-report.com.ve|language=spanish|date=April 21, 2017|accessdate=April 28, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://charts.monitorlatino.com/top20/Colombia/General/20170403|title=Top 20 General Colombia: Del 3 al 9 de Abril, 2017|publisher=Monitor Latino|language=spanish|accessdate=August 18, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.promusicae.es/listas/semana/3395-canciones-semana-15-2017.pdf |title=Top 100 Canciones \u2013 SEMANA 15: del 07.04.2017 al 13.04.2017|publisher=promusicae.es|language=spanish|accessdate=April 12, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Publication\n!Accolade\n!Recipient\n!Year\n!Rank\n!class=\"unsortable\"| {{Tooltip|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n|''[[IBT Media#Assets|Latin Times]]''\n|The 15 Most Addicting Latin Songs of 2015\n|\"S\u00edgueme y Te Sigo\"\n|2015\n|{{center|5}}\n|<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.latintimes.com/pulse/best-2015-15-most-addicting-latin-songs-were-all-rage-year-361670|title=Best Of 2015: 15 Most Addicting Latin Songs That Were All The Rage This Year!|publisher=Latin Times|last=Roiz|first=Jessica Luc\u00eda|date=December 27, 2015|accessdate=January 31, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[NBC News]]''\n|10 Top Latino Songs to Get You Moving\n|\"Shaky Shaky\"\n|2016\n|{{center|1}}\n|<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.nbcnews.com/news/latino/your-holiday-weekend-playlist-10-top-latino-songs-get-you-n686801|title=Your Holiday Weekend Playlist: 10 Top Latino Songs to Get You Moving|publisher=[[NBC News]]|last=Hernandez|first=Ericka|date=November 25, 2016|accessdate=January 31, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''\n|Best Latin Dance Songs of 2016\n|\"Shaky Shaky\"\n|2016\n|{{center|1}}\n|<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/events/year-in-music-2016/7616876/latin-dance-year-end-list-daddy-yankee-shakira|title=All We Want to Do Is Dance: Daddy Yankee, Shakira, Nicky Jam & More Latin Artists Who Got Fans Dancing in 2016|publisher=Billboard|last=Cobo|first=Leila|date=December 13, 2016|accessdate=January 31, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[PopSugar]]''\n|30 Songs That Pretty Much Defined Latin Music in 2016\n|\"Shaky Shaky\"\n|2016\n|{{center|19}}\n|<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.popsugar.com/latina/Best-Latin-Songs-2016-42692301?stream_view=1#photo-42692620|title=30 Songs That Pretty Much Defined Latin Music in 2016|publisher=[[PopSugar]]|last=Martin|first=Macy Daniela|date=December 31, 2016|accessdate=January 31, 2017}}</ref>\n|}\n\n\"S\u00edgueme y Te Sigo\" received a Latin American Music Award for Favorite Urban Song at the [[Latin American Music Awards of 2015|1st Latin American Music Awards]]. It was nominated for [[Latin Grammy Awards]] for [[Latin Grammy Award for Best Urban Song|Best Urban Song]] and [[Latin Grammy Award for Best Urban Performance|Best Urban Performance]] at the [[16th Annual Latin Grammy Awards|16th Latin Grammy Awards]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/6722629/latin-amas-2015-winners-list|title=Latin AMAs Winners List: Enrique Iglesias & Nicky Jam Win Big at Inaugural Awards Show|work=Billboard|last=Cobo|first=Leila|date=October 8, 2015|accessdate=April 29, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/events/latin-awards/6770030/latin-grammys-2015-winners-list|title=Latin Grammys 2015: See the Full Winners List|work=Billboard|date=November 19, 2015|accessdate=April 28, 2017}}</ref>\n\n\"Vaiv\u00e9n\" was nominated for an [[Winter Music Conference#Events|International Dance Music Award]] for Best Latin Dance Track at the 31st International Dance Music Awards and for a [[Lo Nuestro Award for Urban Song of the Year]] at the 29th Lo Nuestro Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wintermusicconference.com/events/idmas/index.php?wmcyear=2016#idmanominees|title=IDMA Winners for the year 2015 presented in 2016|publisher=[[Winter Music Conference]]|accessdate=April 29, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180828183706/http://wintermusicconference.com/events/idmas/index.php?wmcyear=2016#idmanominees|archive-date=August 28, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n\"Shaky Shaky\" received a [[Premios Juventud|Premio Juventud]] for Best Song for Dancing at the [[2017 Premios Juventud|14th Premios Juventud]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.univision.com/especiales/premios-juventud/estos-son-los-ganadores-de-los-premios-juventud-2017|title=Estos son los ganadores de los Premios Juventud 2017|trans-title=These are the winners for the Premios Juventud 2017|publisher=[[Univision]]|language=Spanish|date=July 6, 2017|accessdate=July 7, 2017}}</ref> It was nominated for [[Billboard Latin Music Awards|''Billboard'' Latin Music Awards]] for Hot Latin Song of the Year and Streaming Song of the Year at the 24th ''Billboard'' Latin Music Awards.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7678227/billboard-latin-music-awards-2017-see-the-full-list-of-finalists|title=Billboard Latin Music Awards 2017: See the Full List of Finalists |work=Billboard|last=Cobo|first=Leila|date=February 7, 2017|accessdate=February 12, 2017}}</ref> It also received a [[Billboard Music Award for Top Latin Song|Top Latin Song]] nomination at the [[2017 Billboard Music Awards|24th ''Billboard'' Music Awards]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/bbma/7752631/billboard-music-awards-2017-nominations-full-list|title=Drake, The Chainsmokers Lead Nominees for the 2017 Billboard Music Awards|work=Billboard|date=April 10, 2017|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\nTo be announced.\n\nThe following table is in order of release and is not the official track listing. Some songs may not appear on the final album.\n\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing = \n| extra_column = Producer(s)\n| title1 = S\u00e1bado Rebelde\n| note1 = featuring [[Plan B (duo)|Plan B]]\n| writer1 = {{hlist|Ram\u00f3n Ayala|Orlando Valle|Edwin V\u00e1zquez|Egbert Rosa}}\n| extra1 = {{hlist|Haze|Duran}}\n| length1 = 4:00\n| title2 = [[S\u00edgueme y Te Sigo]]\n| writer2 = {{hlist|R. Ayala|Carlos Ort\u00edz|Luis Ort\u00edz}}\n| extra2 = {{hlist|Chris Jeday|Gaby Music}}\n| length2 = 3:27\n| title3 = Vaiv\u00e9n\n| writer3 = {{hlist|R. Ayala|C. Ort\u00edz|L. Ort\u00edz}}\n| extra3 = {{hlist|Chris Jeday|Gaby Music}}\n| length3 = 3:45\n| title4 = Alerta Roja\n| note4 = featuring [[Zion & Lennox|Zion]], [[Nicky Jam]], [[Arc\u00e1ngel (singer)|Arc\u00e1ngel]], [[De La Ghetto]], Kafu Banton, [[Plan B (duo)|Plan B]], [[J Balvin]], [[Farruko]], [[Cosculluela]], El Micha, [[Brytiago]], Alexio, Mozart La Para, Secreto and [[Gente de Zona]]\n| writer4 = {{hlist|R. Ayala|Nick Rivera|Austin Santos|Rafael Castillo|Zico Garibaldi|O. Valle|E. V\u00e1zquez|Jos\u00e9 Osorio|Carlos Reyes|Jos\u00e9 Cosculluela|Michael Sierra|Bryan Santiago|Victor Rivera|Erickson Fernandez|Odalis P\u00e9rez|Alexander Delgado|Randy Mart\u00ednez}}\n| extra4 = {{hlist|Chris Jeday|Gaby Music|Jumbo}}\n| length4 = 10:23\n| title5 = [[Shaky Shaky]]\n| writer5 = {{hlist|R. Ayala